{"cklb_version":"1.0","id":"e57834a4-214b-11f1-8a56-db6e184814f2","target_data":{"ip_address":"192.168.40.97","mac_address":"00:0C:29:C8:EB:78","target_type":"Computing","host_name":"WKS7-SOTERIA","role":"Workstation","fqdn":"WKS7-SOTERIA."},"title":"SCC Generated CKLB at: 2026-03-16T08:22:08","stigs":[{"stig_name":"Adobe Acrobat Reader DC Continuous Track Security Technical Implementation Guide","uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","rules":[{"rule_id_src":"SV-213168r395811_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Enhanced Security in a Standalone Application.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-213168","title":"SRG-APP-000112"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["V-64919","SV-79409"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:10","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213168","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000005","reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213168","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","rule_id":"SV-213168r395811","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnhancedSecurityStandalone\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bEnhancedSecurityStandalone == 1)\n","ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"8A7CCCFF-6C02-1014-8243-943B7B15D55E","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnhancedSecurityStandalone\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bEnhancedSecurityStandalone is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","discussion":"PDFs have evolved from static pages to complex documents with features such as interactive forms, multimedia content, scripting, and other capabilities. These features leave PDFs vulnerable to malicious scripts or actions that can damage the computer or steal data. The Enhanced security feature protects the computer against these threats by blocking or selectively permitting actions for trusted locations and files.\n\nEnhanced Security determines if a PDF is viewed within a standalone application. A threat to users of Adobe Reader DC is opening a PDF file that contains malicious executable content.\n\nEnhanced Security âhardensâ the application against risky actions: prevents cross domain access, prohibits script and data injection, blocks stream access to XObjects, silent printing, and execution of high privilege JavaScript.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","mitigations":""},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79411","V-64921"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:11","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213169","comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Enhanced Security in a Browser.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213169r395811_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-213169"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-213169","reference_identifier":"3975","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000010","ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bEnhancedSecurityInBrowser == 1)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnhancedSecurityInBrowser\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","rule_id":"SV-213169r395811","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8A7CD31B-6C02-1014-89AA-C9907F9C6E73","mitigations":"","discussion":"PDFs have evolved from static pages to complex documents with features such as interactive forms, multimedia content, scripting, and other capabilities. These features leave PDFs vulnerable to malicious scripts or actions that can damage the computer or steal data. The Enhanced security feature protects the computer against these threats by blocking or selectively permitting actions for trusted locations and files.\n\nEnhanced Security determines if a PDF is viewed within a browser application. A threat to users of Adobe Reader DC is opening a PDF file that contains malicious executable content.\n\nEnhanced Security âhardensâ the application against risky actions: prevents cross domain access, prohibits script and data injection, blocks stream access to XObjects, silent printing, and execution of high privilege JavaScript.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnhancedSecurityInBrowser\nType: REG_DWORD \nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bEnhancedSecurityInBrowser is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD  or does not exist, then this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","documentable":"false"},{"ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-213170r395811","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bProtectedMode == 1)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bProtectedMode\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","uuid":"8A7CE1A6-6C02-1014-9B0F-C3E949D7FBC6","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","discussion":"A threat to users of Adobe Reader DC is opening a PDF file that contains malicious executable content.\n\nProtected mode provides a sandbox capability that prevents malicious PDF files from launching arbitrary executable files, writing to system directories or the Windows registry.\n\nThis isolation of the PDFs reduces the risk of security breaches in areas outside the sandbox.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown \n\nValue Name: bProtectedMode\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bProtectedMode is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79413","V-64923"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:12"},"group_id":"V-213170","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213170r395811_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Protected Mode.","group_tree":{"id":"V-213170","title":"SRG-APP-000112"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-213170","reference_identifier":"3975","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000015"},{"ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","mitigations":"","discussion":"A threat to users of Adobe Reader DC is opening a PDF file that contains malicious executable content.\n\nProtected view restricts Adobe Reader DC functionality, within a sandbox, when a PDF is opened from an untrusted source.\n\nThis isolation of the PDFs reduces the risk of security breaches in areas outside the sandbox.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: iProtectedView\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2\n\nIf the value for iProtectedView is not set to â2â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","uuid":"8A7CE770-6C02-1014-B0C6-F474034822EB","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"rule_id":"SV-213171r395811","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (iProtectedView == 2)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: iProtectedView\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 2","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","group_id_src":"V-213171","reference_identifier":"3975","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000020","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-213171","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:13"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79415","V-64925"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213171","title":"SRG-APP-000112"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213171r395811_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable Protected View."},{"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:14","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213172","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79417","V-64927"],"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-213172"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213172r395811_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must Block Websites.","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","group_id_src":"V-213172","reference_identifier":"3975","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000025","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"rule_id":"SV-213172r395811","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (iURLPerms == 1)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path:\n\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\n\nValue Name: iURLPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf configuring system to allow access to websites, obtain documented ISSO approvals and risk acceptance and set âiURLPermsâ to â0â.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","discussion":"Clicking any link to the Internet poses a potential security risk. Malicious websites can transfer harmful content or silently gather data. Acrobat Reader documents can connect to websites which can pose a potential threat to DoD systems and that functionality must be blocked. However, PDF document workflows that are trusted (e.g., DoD-created) can benefit from leveraging legitimate website access with minimal risk. Therefore, the ISSO may approve of website access and accept the risk if the access provides benefit and is a trusted site or the risk associated with accessing the site has been mitigated.\n\nAdobe Reader must block access to all websites that are not specifically allowed by ISSO risk acceptance.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\n\nValue Name: iURLPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nValue: 0 - only with a documented ISSO risk acceptance\n\nIf the value for âiURLPermsâ is set to â0â and a documented ISSO risk acceptance approving access to websites is provided, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the value for âiURLPermsâ is not set to â1â and âTypeâ configured to âREG_DWORDâ or does not exist, this is a finding.\n","uuid":"8A7CEB79-6C02-1014-8FDE-A2B7DC60EA4A","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-213173"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213173r395811_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must block access to Unknown Websites.","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:15","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213173","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79419","V-64929"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000030","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","group_id_src":"V-213173","reference_identifier":"3975","rule_id":"SV-213173r395811","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (iUnknownURLPerms == 3)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\n\nValue Name: iUnknownURLPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","mitigations":"","discussion":"Because Internet access is a potential security risk, clicking any unknown website link to the Internet poses a potential security risk.\n\nMalicious websites can transfer harmful content or silently gather data.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cDefaultLaunchURLPerms\n\nValue Name: iUnknownURLPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 3\n\nIf the value for iUnknownURLPerms is not set to â3â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","uuid":"8A7CEF56-6C02-1014-9811-A55A603804E8","security_override_guidance":""},{"stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: iFileAttachmentPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for iFileAttachmentPerms is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","discussion":"Attachments represent a potential security risk because they can contain malicious content, open other dangerous files, or launch applications. Certainly file types such as .bin, .exe, .bat, and so on will be recognized as threats.\n\nThis feature prevents users from opening or launching file types other than PDF or FDF and disables the menu option.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","mitigations":"","uuid":"8A7CF330-6C02-1014-BC73-8E45E0C97BD5","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"rule_id":"SV-213174r395811","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: iFileAttachmentPerms\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (iFileAttachmentPerms == 1)\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213174","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000035","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:16","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213174","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79421","V-64931"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-213174","title":"SRG-APP-000112"},"rule_id_src":"SV-213174r395811_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must prevent opening files other than PDF or FDF.","responsibility":""},{"documentable":"false","uuid":"8A7CF74E-6C02-1014-900F-F132FEC5ADFA","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","discussion":"Flash content is commonly hosted on a web page, but it can also be embedded in PDF and other documents. Flash could be used to surreptitious install malware on the end-users computer.\n\nFlash Content restricts Adobe Reader DC not to play Flash content within a PDF.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000112, SRG-APP-000206, SRG-APP-000207, SRG-APP-000209, SRG-APP-000210","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnableFlash\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bEnableFlash is not set to â0â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-213175r395811","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bEnableFlash == 0)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bEnableFlash\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","ccis":["CCI-001166","CCI-001169","CCI-001170","CCI-001662","CCI-001695"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000045","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-213175","reference_identifier":"3975","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213175r395811_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must block Flash Content.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-213175"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79423","V-64933"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:17","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213175"},{"group_id":"V-213176","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:18"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-79425","V-64935"],"severity":"low","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000133","id":"V-213176"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the ability to change the Default Handler.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-213176r395850_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000133","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213176","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000050","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001499"],"fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisablePDFHandlerSwitching\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bDisablePDFHandlerSwitching == 1)\n","rule_id":"SV-213176r395850","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisablePDFHandlerSwitching\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisablePDFHandlerSwitching is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","discussion":"Allowing user to make changes to an application case cause a security risk.\n\nWhen the Default PDF Handler is disabled, the end users will not be able to change the default PDF viewer.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8A7CFB3D-6C02-1014-ABE7-FE1FE2797DD9","documentable":"false"},{"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-213177r766574","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cCloud\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cCloud\n\nValue Name: bAdobeSendPluginToggle\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nConfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt; Administrative Templates &gt; Adobe Reader DC Continuous &gt; Preferences &gt; 'Send and Track plugin' to 'Disabled'.\n\n","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bAdobeSendPluginToggle == 1)\n","uuid":"8A7CFEB2-6C02-1014-898B-B1917C5C95CE","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cCloud\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cCloud\n\nValue Name: bAdobeSendPluginToggle\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bAdobeSendPluginToggle is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.\n\nAdmin Template path: Computer Configuration &gt; Administrative Templates &gt; Adobe Reader DC Continuous &gt; Preferences &gt; 'Send and Track plugin' must be set to 'Disabled'.\n\n","mitigations":"","discussion":"When enabled, Adobe Send and Track button appears in Outlook. When an email is composed it enables the ability to send large files as public links through Outlook. The attached files can be uploaded to the Adobe Document Cloud and public links to the files are inserted in the email body.","documentable":"false","severity":"low","legacy_ids":["SV-79427","V-64937"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:19"},"group_id":"V-213177","rule_id_src":"SV-213177r766574_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the Adobe Send and Track plugin for Outlook.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-213177","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213177","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000055"},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000060","group_id_src":"V-213178","reference_identifier":"3975","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213178r395853_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable all service access to Document Cloud Services.","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-213178","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79429","V-64939"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-213178","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:20"},"documentable":"false","uuid":"8A7D023E-6C02-1014-BD86-D27CC81CB659","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","discussion":"By default, Adobe online services are tightly integrated in Adobe Reader DC. With the integration of Adobe Document Cloud, disabling this feature prevents the risk of additional attack vectors.\n\nWithin Adobe Reader DC, the Adobe Cloud resources require a paid subscription for each service.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleAdobeDocumentServices\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bToggleAdobeDocumentServices is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-213178r395853","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bToggleAdobeDocumentServices == 1)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleAdobeDocumentServices\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bTogglePrefsSync\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bTogglePrefsSync is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","discussion":"By default, Adobe online services are tightly integrated in Adobe Reader DC. When the Adobe Cloud synchronization is disabled it prevents the synchronization of desktop preferences across devices on which the user is signed in with an Adobe ID (including phones).","mitigations":"","uuid":"8A7D05A5-6C02-1014-998E-C6C7760AC2B7","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-213179r395853","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bTogglePrefsSync\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bTogglePrefsSync == 1)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000065","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213179","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-213179","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_id_src":"SV-213179r395853_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Cloud Synchronization.","responsibility":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-213179","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:21","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79431","V-64941"]},{"fix_text":"\"Configure the following registry value:\n\nFor 32 bit:\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer \n\nFor 64 bit:\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer\n\nValue Name: DisableMaintenance\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (DisableMaintenance == 1, 32-bit)\nTest            :   true (DisableMaintenance == 1, 64-bit)\n","rule_id":"SV-213180r395853","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"documentable":"false","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: \n\nFor 32 bit:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer\n\nFor 64 bit:\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Wow6432Node\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Installer\n\nValue Name: DisableMaintenance\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for DisableMaintenance is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","discussion":"When Repair Installation is disabled the user does not have the option (Help Menu) or functional to repair an Adobe Reader DC install.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8A7D0926-6C02-1014-817E-D597AD59CF6C","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-213180"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the Adobe Repair Installation.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-213180r395853_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-213180","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:22"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-79433","V-64943"],"severity":"low","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000070","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213180"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79435","V-64945"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-213181","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:23"},"rule_id_src":"SV-213181r395853_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable 3rd Party Web Connectors.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-213181"},"reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213181","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000075","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-213181r395853","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleWebConnectors\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bToggleWebConnectors == 1)\n","uuid":"8A7D0C75-6C02-1014-A9C9-BDA4B86A06D4","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleWebConnectors\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bToggleWebConnectors is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","discussion":"When 3rd Party Web Connectors are disabled it prevents the configuration of Adobe Reader DC access to third party services for file storage.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false"},{"ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","mitigations":"","discussion":"Products that don't provide the full set of features by default provide the user the opportunity to upgrade. Acrobat Upsell displays message which encourage the user to upgrade the product. For example, Reader users can purchase additional tools and features, and Acrobat Reader users can upgrade to Acrobat Professional.","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following:\n\nHKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bAcroSuppressUpsell\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1   \n\nIf the value for bAcroSuppressUpsell is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.\n","uuid":"8A7D0FC3-6C02-1014-9409-8ADC8D2B0DF9","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-213182r395853","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bAcroSuppressUpsell == 1)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\n\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bAcroSuppressUpsell\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1   ","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id_src":"V-213182","reference_identifier":"3975","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000080","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:37","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213182","severity":"low","legacy_ids":["SV-80539","V-66049"],"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-213182"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213182r395853_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Acrobat Upsell."},{"group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213183","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000085","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:24","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213183","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-79437","V-64947"],"severity":"low","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-213183"},"rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Adobe Send for Signature.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-213183r395853_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleAdobeSign\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bToggleAdobeSign is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The Adobe Document Cloud sign service allows users to send documents online for signature and sign from anywhere or any device. The signed documents are stored in the Adobe Cloud. The Adobe Document Cloud sign service is a paid subscription.\n\nWhen Adobe Send for Signature is disabled users will not be allowed to utilize the Adobe Document Cloud sign function.","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8A7D1385-6C02-1014-A193-E065871548D8","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bToggleAdobeSign\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bToggleAdobeSign == 1)\n","rule_id":"SV-213183r395853"},{"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-213184"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable access to Webmail.","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213184r395853_rule","group_id":"V-213184","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:25","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-79439","V-64949"],"severity":"medium","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000090","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-213184","reference_identifier":"3975","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bDisableWebmail == 1)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cWebmailProfiles\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWebmailProfiles\n\nValue Name: bDisableWebmail\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","rule_id":"SV-213184r395853","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"documentable":"false","discussion":"When Webmail is disabled the user cannot configure a webmail account to send an open PDF document as an attachment. Users should have the ability to send documents as Microsoft Outlook attachments. The difference is that Outlook must be configured by the administrator on the local machine.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cWebmailProfiles\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWebmailProfiles\n\nValue Name: bDisableWebmail\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisableWebmail is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8A7D16C8-6C02-1014-B303-87900157DCDD"},{"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000100","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id_src":"V-213185","reference_identifier":"3975","group_tree":{"id":"V-213185","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213185r395853_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Online SharePoint Access.","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:26","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213185","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79441","V-64951"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","discussion":"Disabling SharePoint disables or removes the userâs ability to add a SharePoint account access controls the application's ability to detect that a file came from a SharePoint server, and disables the check-out prompt.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nIf configured to an approved DoD SharePoint Server, this is NA.\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cSharePoint\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cSharePoint\n\nValue Name: bDisableSharePointFeatures\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisableSharePointFeatures is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","uuid":"8A7D1A0F-6C02-1014-B3B5-AFE527666B95","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-213185r395853","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bDisableSharePointFeatures == 1)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cSharePoint\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cSharePoint\n\nValue Name: bDisableSharePointFeatures\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"]},{"responsibility":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the Adobe Welcome Screen.","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213186r395853_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-213186"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79443","V-64953"],"severity":"low","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:27"},"group_id":"V-213186","comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000115","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-213186","reference_identifier":"3975","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bShowWelcomeScreen == 0)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cWelcomeScreen\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWelcomeScreen\n\nValue Name: bShowWelcomeScreen\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","rule_id":"SV-213186r395853","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8A7D1D52-6C02-1014-A907-B8782645933E","mitigations":"","discussion":"The Adobe Reader DC Welcome screen can be distracting and also has online links to the Adobe quick tips website, tutorials, blogs and community forums.\n\nWhen the Adobe Reader DC Welcome screen is disabled the Welcome screen will not be populated on application startup.","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cWelcomeScreen\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cWelcomeScreen\n\nValue Name: bShowWelcomeScreen\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bShowWelcomeScreen is not set to â0â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7"},{"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bUpdater == 0)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bUpdater\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","rule_id":"SV-213187r395853","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8A7D209F-6C02-1014-9F8C-B283D6DF37B1","discussion":"By default, Adobe online services are tightly integrated into Adobe Reader DC. Disabling Service Upgrades disables both updates to the product's web-plugin components as well as all services without exception, including any online sign-in screen.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Name \"cServices\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\\cServices\n\nValue Name: bUpdater\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bUpdater is not set to â0â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable Service Upgrades.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213187r395853_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-213187"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-79445","V-64955"],"severity":"low","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:28","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-213187","comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000120","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-213187","reference_identifier":"3975","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-80157","V-65667"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-213188","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:30","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-213188r400006_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the ability to add Trusted Files and Folders.","group_tree":{"id":"V-213188","title":"SRG-APP-000380"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-213188","reference_identifier":"3975","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000380","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000315","ccis":["CCI-001813"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-213188r400006","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bDisableTrustedFolders == 1)\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisableTrustedFolders\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","uuid":"8A7D258A-6C02-1014-827F-F185596D4230","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","mitigations":"","discussion":"Privileged Locations allow the user to selectively trust files, folders, and hosts to bypass some security restrictions, such as enhanced security and protected view. By default, the user can create privileged locations through the GUI.\n\nDisabling Trusted Files and Folders disables and locks the end user's ability to add folders and files as a privileged location prevents them from assigning trust and thereby exempting that location from enhanced security restrictions.","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisableTrustedFolders\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisableTrustedFolders is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","documentable":"false"},{"documentable":"false","uuid":"8A7D2A44-6C02-1014-A84E-898EC7D0A099","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisableTrustedSites\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bDisableTrustedSites is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Privileged Locations allow the user to selectively trust files, folders, and hosts to bypass some security restrictions, such as enhanced security and protected view. By default, the user can create privileged locations through the GUI.\n\nDisabling IE Trusts to Privileged Locations disables and locks the end user's ability to treat IE trusted sites as a privileged location prevents them from assigning trust and thereby exempting that location from enhanced security restrictions.","rule_id":"SV-213189r400006","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Policies\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\FeatureLockDown\n\nValue Name: bDisableTrustedSites\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (bDisableTrustedSites == 1)\n","ccis":["CCI-001813"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000320","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213189","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000380","rule_id_src":"SV-213189r400006_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable the ability to elevate IE Trusts to Privileged Locations.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-213189","title":"SRG-APP-000380"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-80159","V-65669"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-213189","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.adobe.reader:def:31","href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval.xml"}},{"uuid":"8A7D2DC8-6C02-1014-A45B-B7CA893DE5FD","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"cDigSig\" and \"cEUTLDownload\" are not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cEUTLDownload\n\nValue Name: bLoadSettingsFromURL \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bLoadSettingsFromURL is not set to â0â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"By default, the user can update European certificates from an Adobe server through the GUI.\n\nWhen uploading European certificates is disabled, it prevents the automatic download and installation of certificates and disables and locks the end user's ability to upload those certificates.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-002470"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-213190r400378","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"cDigSig\" and \"cEUTLDownload\" are not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cEUTLDownload\n\nValue Name: bLoadSettingsFromURL \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Adobe Reader DC must disable periodical uploading of European certificates.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cEUTLDownload\\bLoadSettingsFromURL'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213190","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000427","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000330","severity":"low","legacy_ids":["SV-80163","V-65673"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.adobe.reader:def:213190"},"group_id":"V-213190","rule_id_src":"SV-213190r400378_rule","status":"open","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable periodical uploading of European certificates.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000427","id":"V-213190"}},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-002470"],"rule_id":"SV-213191r400378","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Adobe Reader DC must disable periodical uploading of Adobe certificates.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cAdobeDownload\\bLoadSettingsFromURL'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"cDigSig\" and \"cAdobeDownload\" are not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cAdobeDownload\n\nValue Name: bLoadSettingsFromURL \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","discussion":"By default, the user can update Adobe certificates from an Adobe server through the GUI.\n\nWhen uploading Adobe certificates is disabled, it prevents the automatic download and installation of certificates and disables and locks the end user's ability to upload those certificates.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"cDigSig\" and \"cAdobeDownload\" are not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\Security\\cDigSig\\cAdobeDownload\n\nValue Name: bLoadSettingsFromURL \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0\n\nIf the value for bLoadSettingsFromURL is not set to â0â and Type configured to REG_DWORD or does not exist, then this is a finding.","uuid":"8A7D31DC-6C02-1014-9B79-E09BB4264CCA","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.adobe.reader:def:213191"},"group_id":"V-213191","severity":"low","legacy_ids":["SV-80165","V-65675"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-213191","title":"SRG-APP-000427"},"false_positives":"","status":"open","rule_id_src":"SV-213191r400378_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must disable periodical uploading of Adobe certificates.","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000427","group_id_src":"V-213191","reference_identifier":"3975","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000335","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000340","group_id_src":"V-213192","reference_identifier":"3975","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","status":"not_reviewed","rule_id_src":"SV-213192r400525_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must have the latest Security-related Software Updates installed.","group_tree":{"id":"V-213192","title":"SRG-APP-000456"},"false_positives":"","severity":"high","legacy_ids":["SV-80167","V-65677"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-213192","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.adobe.reader:questionnaire:4901"},"documentable":"false","uuid":"8A7D3567-6C02-1014-9940-FFEC83272BDE","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously.\n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw).\n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality, will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means that the time period utilized must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may be dependent upon the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.\n\nThe application will be configured to check for and install security-relevant software updates within an identified time period from the availability of the update. The specific time period will be defined by an authoritative source (e.g., IAVM, CTOs, DTMs, and STIGs).","mitigations":"","check_content":"Determine the method for doing this (e.g., connection to a WSUS server, local procedure, auto update, etc.).\n\nOpen Adobe Acrobat Reader DC.\n\nNavigate to and click on Help &gt;&gt; About Adobe Acrobat Reader DC.\n\nVerify that the latest security-related software updates by Adobe are being applied.\n\nIf the latest security-related software updates by Adobe are not being applied, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-213192r400525","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-213192, SV-213192r400525, SRG-APP-000456)\n","fix_text":"Apply the latest security-related software updates to the Adobe Acrobat Reader application.","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"documentable":"false","uuid":"8A7D38E0-6C02-1014-87B3-82FFB675DC05","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8A7C5EA4-6C02-1014-BD4E-C87CC747D2B7","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the following registry configuration:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"bFIPSMode\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nUtilizing the Registry Editor, navigate to the following: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\AVGeneral\n\nValue Name: bFIPSMode \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1\n\nIf the value for bFIPSMode is not set to â1â and Type configured to REG_DWORD does not exist, then this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Use of weak or untested encryption algorithms undermines the purposes of utilizing encryption to protect data. The application must implement cryptographic modules adhering to the higher standards approved by the federal government since this provides assurance they have been tested and validated.","rule_id":"SV-213193r400876","fix_text":"Configure the following registry value:\n\nNote: The Key Names \"bFIPSMode\" is not created by default in the Adobe Reader DC install and must be created.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\nRegistry Path: \\Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\AVGeneral\n\nValue Name: bFIPSMode \nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 1","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:14\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Adobe Reader DC must enable FIPS mode.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Adobe\\Acrobat Reader\\DC\\AVGeneral\\bFIPSMode'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"ARDC-CN-000345","reference_identifier":"3975","group_id_src":"V-213193","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000514","rule_id_src":"SV-213193r400876_rule","status":"open","rule_title":"Adobe Reader DC must enable FIPS mode.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000514","id":"V-213193"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-80169","V-65679"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_V2R4_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV11-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.adobe.reader:def:213193"},"group_id":"V-213193"}],"reference_identifier":"3975","release_info":"Release: 1 Benchmark Date: 23 Jul 2021","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","display_name":"Adobe Acrobat Reader DC Continuous Track","size":26,"stig_id":"Adobe_Acrobat_Reader_DC_Continuous_Track_STIG","version":"2"},{"classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","release_info":"Release: 11 Benchmark Date: 02 Jul 2025","display_name":"Google Chrome Current Windows","uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","stig_name":"Google Chrome Current Windows Security Technical Implementation Guide","reference_identifier":"4081","rules":[{"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-221558"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221558r960804_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Firewall traversal from remote host must be disabled.","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240001"},"group_id":"V-221558","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57545","V-44711"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0001","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","group_id_src":"V-221558","reference_identifier":"4081","rule_id":"SV-221558r960804","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable firewall traversal)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative\\Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Remote Access\n Policy Name: Enable firewall traversal from remote access host\n Policy State: Disabled\n Policy Value: N/A","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","discussion":"Remote connections should never be allowed that bypass the firewall, as there is no way to verify if they can be trusted. Enables usage of STUN and relay servers when remote clients are trying to establish a connection to this machine. If this setting is enabled, then remote clients can discover and connect to this machine even if they are separated by a firewall. If this setting is disabled and outgoing UDP connections are filtered by the firewall, then this machine will only allow connections from client machines within the local network. If this policy is left not set the setting will be enabled.\t","mitigations":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If RemoteAccessHostFirewallTraversal is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows registry:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the RemoteAccessHostFirewallTraversal value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.  \n","uuid":"8E425D35-6C02-1014-B2C4-A831EF644932","security_override_guidance":""},{"weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221559","rule_version":"DTBC-0002","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240002","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221559","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57557","V-44723"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-221559"},"rule_id_src":"SV-221559r961083_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Site tracking users location must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:               \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy             \n   2. If DefaultGeolocationSetting is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the DefaultGeolocationSetting value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n","mitigations":"","discussion":"Website tracking is the practice of gathering information as to which websites were accesses by a browser. The common method of doing this is to have a website create a tracking cookie on the browser.   If the information of what sites are being accessed is made available to unauthorized persons, this violates confidentiality requirements, and over time poses a significant OPSEC issue. This policy setting allows you to set whether websites are allowed to track the userâs physical location. Tracking the userâs physical location can be allowed by default, denied by default or the user can be asked every time a website requests the physical location.\t\n   1 = Allow sites to track the userâs physical location\t\n   2 = Do not allow any site to track the userâs physical location\t\n   3 = Ask whenever a site wants to track the userâs physical location","uuid":"8E426364-6C02-1014-A07D-ACDFE91FA19F","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"rule_id":"SV-221559r961083","fix_text":"Windows group policy:    \n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\\    \n   Policy Name: Default geolocation setting    \n   Policy State: Enabled    \n   Policy Value: Do not allow any site to track the users' physical location\n\n","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable tracking user's location)\n"},{"rule_id":"SV-221561r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable pop-ups)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\\\n    Policy Name: Default popups setting\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: Do not allow any site to show popups\n\n","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"8E426761-6C02-1014-8152-E95033CF3D8C","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","discussion":"Chrome allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and pop-ups that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to â2â to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the pop-up windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.  If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.  If this policy is left not set, 'BlockPopups' will be used and the user will be able to change it.    \n   1 = Allow all sites to show pop-ups    \n   2 = Do not allow any site to show pop-ups","mitigations":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If DefaultPopupsSetting is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the value name DefaultPopupsSetting does not exist or its value data is not set to 2, then this is a finding.\n\nNote:  If AO Approved exceptions to this rule have been enabled, this is not a finding.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221561r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Sites ability to show pop-ups must be disabled.","group_tree":{"id":"V-221561","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57553","V-44719"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-221561","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240004","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0004","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-221561","reference_identifier":"4081","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Extensions\\\n Policy Name: Configure extension installation blocklist\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: *","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Extensions installation are blocklisted by default)\n","rule_id":"SV-221562r960879","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If ExtensionInstallBlocklist is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to * under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallBlocklist\n 3. If the a registry value name of 1 does not exist under that key or its value is not set to *, then this is a finding. ","discussion":"Extensions are developed by third party sources and are designed to extend Google Chrome's functionality. An extension can be made by anyone, to do and access almost anything on a system; this means they pose a high risk to any system that would allow all extensions to be installed by default. Allows you to specify which extensions the users can NOT install. Extensions already installed will be removed if blocklisted. A blocklist value of '*' means all extensions are blocklisted unless they are explicitly listed in the allowlist. If this policy is left not set the user can install any extension in Google Chrome.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E426B17-6C02-1014-9282-E365BA82FD74","documentable":"false","group_id":"V-221562","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240005","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-57561","V-44727"],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221562","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"rule_title":"Extensions installation must be blocklisted by default.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221562r960879_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221562","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0005","third_party_tools":""},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0006","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221563","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","weight":"10.0","rule_title":"Extensions that are approved for use must be allowlisted.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221563r1015468_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-221563"},"legacy_ids":["SV-57563","V-44729"],"severity":"low","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240006"},"group_id":"V-221563","comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E426EDA-6C02-1014-AED9-93A9A441A754","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If ExtensionInstallAllowlist is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdf or a list of administrator approved extension IDs, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to the key HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\ExtensionInstallAllowlist\n3. If the ExtensionInstallAllowlist key is not set to 1 and oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdf or a list of administrator-approved extension IDs, then this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The allowlist should only contain organizationally approved extensions. This is to prevent a user from accidently allowlisitng a malicious extension. This policy allows you to specify which extensions are not subject to the blacklist. A blacklist value of â*â means all extensions are blacklisted and users can only install extensions listed in the allowlist. By default, no extensions are allowlisted. If all extensions have been blacklisted by policy, then the allowlist policy can be used to allow specific extensions to be installed. Administrators should determine which extensions should be allowed to be installed by their users. If no extensions are allowlisted, then no extensions can be installed when combined with blacklisting all extensions.","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Extensions\\\nPolicy Name: Configure extension installation allowlist\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdf\n\nNote: oiigbmnaadbkfbmpbfijlflahbdbdgdfis the extension ID for scriptno (a commonly used Chrome extension), other extension IDs may vary.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Extensions that are approved for use are allowlisted)\n","rule_id":"SV-221563r1015468","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0007","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-221564","reference_identifier":"4081","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221564r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The default search providers name must be set.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221564"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57567","V-44733"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240007"},"group_id":"V-221564","documentable":"false","uuid":"8E42728E-6C02-1014-A952-B8498AB9427A","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","mitigations":"","discussion":"Specifies the name of the default search provider that is to be used, if left empty or not set, the host name specified by the search URL will be used. This policy is only considered if the 'DefaultSearchProviderEnabled' policy is enabled. When doing internet searches it is important to use an encrypted connection via https.","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If DefaultSearchProviderName is displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to an organization approved encrypted search provider that corresponds to the encrypted search provider set in DTBC-0008(ex. Google Encrypted, Bing Encrypted) under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the DefaultSearchProviderName value name does not exist or it is not set to an organization approved encrypted search provider that corresponds to the encrypted search provider set in DTBC-0008(ex. Google Encrypted, Bing Encrypted), then this is a finding.\n","rule_id":"SV-221564r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Set default search provider name)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Default search provider\\\n    Policy Name: Default search provider name\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: set to an organization approved encrypted search provider that corresponds to the encrypted search provider set in DTBC-0008(ex. Google Encrypted, Bing Encrypted)\n\n","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"documentable":"false","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nUniversal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy.\n2. If DefaultSearchProviderSearchURL is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to an organization-approved encrypted search string (ex. https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms} or https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms} ) under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\.\n3. If the DefaultSearchProviderSearchURL value name does not exist or its value data is not set to an organization-approved encrypted search string (ex. https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms} or https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms} ), this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Specifies the URL of the search engine used when doing a default search. The URL should contain the string '{searchTerms}', which will be replaced at query time by the terms the user is searching for. This option must be set when the 'DefaultSearchProviderEnabled' policy is enabled and will only be respected if this is the case.  When doing internet searches it is important to use an encrypted connection via https.","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E427619-6C02-1014-8DDB-BD95F3FA3DC6","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nWindows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Default search provider\\.\n- Policy Name: Default search provider search URL\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value: Must be set to an organization-approved encrypted search string \n(ex. https://www.google.com/search?q={searchTerms} or https://www.bing.com/search?q={searchTerms} )","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The default search provider URL must be set to perform encrypted searches.)\n","rule_id":"SV-221565r960963","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0008","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221565","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221565"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The default search provider URL must be set to perform encrypted searches.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221565r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-221565","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:221565"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-57569","V-44735"],"severity":"medium"},{"uuid":"8E4279D4-6C02-1014-9D0D-AA8B5871A461","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","mitigations":"","discussion":"Policy enables the use of a default search provider. If you enable this setting, a default search is performed when the user types text in the omnibox that is not a URL. You can specify the default search provider to be used by setting the rest of the default search policies. If these are left empty, the user can choose the default provider. If you disable this setting, no search is performed when the user enters non-URL text in the omnibox. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, the default search provider is enabled, and the user will be able to set the search provider list.","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If DefaultSearchProviderEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to true under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the DefaultSearchProviderEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n\nNote: This policy will only display in the chrome://policy tab on domain joined systems. On standalone systems, the policy will not display.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221566r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Enable default search provider)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Default search provider\\\n    Policy Name: Enable the default search provider\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: N/A\n\n","group_id_src":"V-221566","reference_identifier":"4081","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0009","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57571","V-44737"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240009","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221566","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221566r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Default search provider must be enabled.","group_tree":{"id":"V-221566","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":""},{"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:           \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy           \n   2. If PasswordManagerEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the PasswordManagerEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","mitigations":"","discussion":"Enables saving passwords and using saved passwords in Google Chrome. Malicious sites may take advantage of this feature by using hidden fields gain access to the stored information. If you enable this setting, users can have Google Chrome memorize passwords and provide them automatically the next time they log in to a site. If you disable this setting, users are not able to save passwords or use already saved passwords. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, this will be enabled but the user will be able to change it. ListPassword manager should not be used as it stores passwords locally.","uuid":"8E427D61-6C02-1014-8F01-D694BA790F78","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-221567r960963","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Password Manager\\\nPolicy Name: Enable Saving Passwords to the Password Manager\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable Password Manager)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0011","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221567","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221567","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_id_src":"SV-221567r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Password Manager must be disabled.","responsibility":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-221567","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240011"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57575","V-44741"]},{"check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If BackgroundModeEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column and it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the BackgroundModeEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","mitigations":"","discussion":"Determines whether a Google Chrome process is started on OS login that keeps running when the last browser window is closed, allowing background apps to remain active. The background process displays an icon in the system tray and can always be closed from there. If this policy is set to True, background mode is enabled and cannot be controlled by the user in the browser settings. If this policy is set to False, background mode is disabled and cannot be controlled by the user in the browser settings. If this policy is left unset, background mode is initially disabled and can be controlled by the user in the browser settings.' - Google Chrome Administrators Policy ListThis setting, if enabled, allows Google Chrome to run at all times. There is two reasons that this is not wanted. First, it can tie up system resources that might otherwise be needed. Second, it does not make it obvious to the user that it is running and poorly written extensions could cause instability on the system.","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E4280D4-6C02-1014-98B8-F81029290D4F","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Continue running background apps when Google Chrome is closed\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable background processing)\n","rule_id":"SV-221570r960921","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221570","rule_version":"DTBC-0017","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240017"},"group_id":"V-221570","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-57587","V-44753"],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-221570"},"rule_title":"Background processing must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221570r960921_rule","status":"not_a_finding"},{"rule_id":"SV-221571r987620","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable Google data synchronization)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Disable synchronization of data with Google\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001374"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","mitigations":"","discussion":"Disables data synchronization in Google Chrome using Google-hosted synchronization services and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set the user will be able to enable Google Sync.  Google Sync is used to sync information between different user devices, this data is then stored on Google owned servers. The synced data may consist of information such as email, calendars, viewing history, etc. This feature must be disabled because the organization does not have control over the servers the data is stored on.","check_content":"Universal method:        \n  1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n  2. If SyncDisabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to true under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the SyncDisabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n","uuid":"8E42847B-6C02-1014-A24D-C9E8FD60BE04","security_override_guidance":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000047","id":"V-221571"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221571r987620_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Google Data Synchronization must be disabled.","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240020","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221571","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57593","V-44759"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0020","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000047","group_id_src":"V-221571","reference_identifier":"4081"},{"documentable":"false","uuid":"8E428810-6C02-1014-8113-BF1342ECA1F5","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","discussion":"Each access to a URL is handled by the browser according to the URL's \"scheme\". The \"scheme\" of a URL is the section before the \":\". The term \"protocol\" is often mistakenly used for a \"scheme\". The difference is that the scheme is how the browser handles a URL and the protocol is how the browser communicates with a service.  If a scheme or its associated protocol used by a browser is insecure or obsolete, vulnerabilities can be exploited resulting in exposed data or unrestricted access to the browser's system.   The browser must be configured to disable the use of insecure and obsolete schemas (protocols).\nThis policy disables the listed protocol schemes in Google Chrome, URLs using a scheme from this list will not load and cannot be navigated to. If this policy is left not set or the list is empty all schemes will be accessible in Google Chrome.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy.\n2. If URLBlocklist is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to javascript://* under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\URLBlocklist.\n3. If the URLBlocklist key does not exist, or the does not contain entries 1 set to javascript://*, this is a finding.\n\n","rule_id":"SV-221572r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The URL protocol schema javascript is disabled)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc. \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Block access to a list of URLs.\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value 1: javascript://*","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0021","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-221572","reference_identifier":"4081","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221572r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The URL protocol schema javascript must be disabled.","group_tree":{"id":"V-221572","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57595","V-44761"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240021","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221572"},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0023","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221573","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000047","rule_id_src":"SV-221573r987620_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Cloud print sharing must be disabled.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221573","title":"SRG-APP-000047"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57599","V-44765"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-221573","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240023","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"documentable":"false","uuid":"8E428B76-6C02-1014-A31B-86CB72CAB5E9","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If CloudPrintProxyEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the CloudPrintProxyEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Policy enables Google Chrome to act as a proxy between Google Cloud Print and legacy printers connected to the machine. If this setting is enabled or not configured, users can enable the cloud print proxy by authentication with their Google account. If this setting is disabled, users cannot enable the proxy, and the machine will not be allowed to share itâs printers with Google Cloud Print. If this policy is not set, this will be enabled but the user will be able to change it.","rule_id":"SV-221573r987620","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Printing\n Policy Name: Enable Google Cloud Print proxy\n Policy State: Disabled\n Policy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable cloud print sharing)\n","ccis":["CCI-001374"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221574","rule_version":"DTBC-0025","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240025","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221574","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57603","V-44769"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221574","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_id_src":"SV-221574r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Network prediction must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n2. If \"NetworkPredictionOptions\" is not displayed under the âPolicy Nameâ column or it is not set to \"2\" under the âPolicy Valueâ column, this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the \"NetworkPredictionOptions\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2,\" this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Enables network prediction in Google Chrome and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, this will be disabled but the user will be able to change it.","uuid":"8E428F35-6C02-1014-AF26-FC9D3F6EF57B","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"rule_id":"SV-221574r961863","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable network prediction\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not predict network actions on any network connection","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable network prediction)\n"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57605","V-44771"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-221575","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240026"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221575r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Metrics reporting to Google must be disabled.","group_tree":{"id":"V-221575","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-221575","reference_identifier":"4081","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0026","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-221575r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable Google metrics reporting)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Enable reporting of usage and crash-related data\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","uuid":"8E4292BB-6C02-1014-AD0B-DE0110CAA277","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","mitigations":"","discussion":"Enables anonymous reporting of usage and crash-related data about Google Chrome to Google and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable this setting, anonymous reporting of usage and crash-related data is sent to Google. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you disable this setting, anonymous reporting of usage and crash-related data is never sent to Google. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set the setting will be what the user chose upon installation / first run.","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If MetricsReportingEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the MetricsReportingEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n\nNote: This policy will only display in the chrome://policy tab on domain joined systems. On standalone systems, the policy will not display.","documentable":"false"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-57607","V-44773"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-221576","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240027","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"rule_title":"Search suggestions must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221576r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221576"},"reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221576","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0027","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Enable search suggestions\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Enable search suggestion)\n","rule_id":"SV-221576r960963","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E429627-6C02-1014-A3FB-D78EE7F05527","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If SearchSuggestEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the SearchSuggestEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","discussion":"Search suggestion should be disabled as it could lead to searches being conducted that were never intended to be made. Enables search suggestions in Google Chrome's omnibox and prevents users from changing this setting. If you enable this setting, search suggestions are used. If you disable this setting, search suggestions are never used. If you enable or disable this setting, users cannot change or override this setting in Google Chrome. If this policy is left not set, this will be enabled but the user will be able to change it.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false"},{"documentable":"false","uuid":"8E42998B-6C02-1014-A940-98320569C850","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If ImportSavedPasswords is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to false under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the ImportSavedPasswords value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Importing of saved passwords should be disabled as it could lead to unencrypted account passwords stored on the system from another browser to be viewed. This policy forces the saved passwords to be imported from the previous default browser if enabled. If enabled, this policy also affects the import dialog. If disabled, the saved passwords are not imported. If it is not set, the user may be asked whether to import, or importing may happen automatically.","rule_id":"SV-221577r960963","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n   Policy Name: Import saved passwords from default browser on first run\n   Policy State: Disabled\n   Policy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Password history=VAR)\n","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0029","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221577","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id_src":"SV-221577r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Importing of saved passwords must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221577"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57609","V-44775"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240029"},"group_id":"V-221577"},{"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","mitigations":"","discussion":"Incognito mode allows the user to browse the Internet without recording their browsing history/activity.  From a forensics perspective, this is unacceptable.  Best practice requires that browser history is retained.  The \"IncognitoModeAvailability\" setting controls whether the user may utilize Incognito mode in Google Chrome. If 'Enabled' is selected or the policy is left unset, pages may be opened in Incognito mode. If 'Disabled' is selected, pages may not be opened in Incognito mode. If 'Forced' is selected, pages may be opened ONLY in Incognito mode.   \n   0 = Incognito mode available.    \n   1 = Incognito mode disabled.    \n   2 = Incognito mode forced.","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If IncognitoModeAvailability is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 1 under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the IncognitoModeAvailability value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n","uuid":"8E429CCD-6C02-1014-A761-B410DB2EA4D1","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-221578r960864","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable incognito mode)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Incognito mode availability\n    Policy State: Enabled\n    Policy Value: Incognito mode disabled","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0030","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","group_id_src":"V-221578","reference_identifier":"4081","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000080","id":"V-221578"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221578r960864_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Incognito mode must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-221578","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240030","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57611","V-44777"]},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0037","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221579","group_title":"SRG-APP-000605","weight":"10.0","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Online revocation checks must be performed.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221579r961893_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000605","id":"V-221579"},"legacy_ids":["SV-57623","V-44789"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-221579","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240037"},"comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42A021-6C02-1014-9E9F-C90C797EB21A","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If EnableOnlineRevocationChecks is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to true under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the EnableOnlineRevocationChecks value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1, then this is a finding.\n","discussion":"By setting this policy to true, the previous behavior is restored and online OCSP/CRL checks will be performed. If the policy is not set, or is set to false, then Chrome will not perform online revocation checks. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n Policy Name: Enable online OCSP/CRL checks\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Perform online revocation checks)\n","rule_id":"SV-221579r961893","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221580","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Safe Browsing must be enabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221580r961083_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240038","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221580","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-57625","V-44791"],"severity":"medium","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0038","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221580","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Safe Browsing Settings\n Policy Name: Safe Browsing Protection Level\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: \"(1) Safe Browsing is active in the standard mode\", or \"(2) Safe Browsing is active in the enhanced mode. This mode provides better security, but requires sharing more browsing information with Google\".","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Safe Browsing is enabled)\n","rule_id":"SV-221580r961083","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"documentable":"false","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If SafeBrowsingProtectionLevel is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 1 or 2 under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the SafeBrowsingProtectionLevel value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 1 or 2, then this is a finding.","discussion":"Allows you to control whether Google Chrome's Safe Browsing feature is enabled and the mode it operates in.\n\nIf this policy is set to 'NoProtection' (value 0), Safe Browsing is never active.\n\nIf this policy is set to 'StandardProtection' (value 1, which is the default), Safe Browsing is always active in the standard mode.\n\nIf this policy is set to 'EnhancedProtection' (value 2), Safe Browsing is always active in the enhanced mode, which provides better security, but requires sharing more browsing information with Google.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42A367-6C02-1014-91B7-8EF2FA28AE28"},{"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0039","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221581","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221581","title":"SRG-APP-000231"},"rule_id_src":"SV-221581r961128_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Browser history must be saved.","responsibility":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240039"},"group_id":"V-221581","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-57627","V-44793"],"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:        \n   1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy        \n   2. If the policy 'SavingBrowserHistoryDisabled' is not shown or is not set to false, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n   1. Start regedit\n   2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n   3. If the SavingBrowserHistoryDisabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, then this is a finding.\n","discussion":"This policy disables saving browser history in Google Chrome and prevents users from changing this setting. If this setting is enabled, browsing history is not saved. If this setting is disabled or not set, browsing history is saved.","mitigations":"","uuid":"8E42A9D5-6C02-1014-A4EC-F9523A6CEE0B","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-221581r961128","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n   1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc   \n   2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n    Policy Name: Disable saving browser history\n    Policy State: Disabled\n    Policy Value:  N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Save browser history)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001199"]},{"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000456","id":"V-221584"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The version of Google Chrome running on the system must be a supported version.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221584r961683_rule","status":"not_reviewed","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:questionnaire:4301","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-ocil.xml"},"group_id":"V-221584","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-57639","V-44805"],"severity":"medium","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0050","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221584","fix_text":"Install a supported version of Google Chrome.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-221584, SV-221584r961683, SRG-APP-000456)\n","rule_id":"SV-221584r961683","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"documentable":"false","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://settings/help\n2. Cross-reference the build information displayed with the Google Chrome site to identify, at minimum, the oldest supported build available.  As of July 2019, this is 74.x.x.\n3. If the installed version of Chrome is not supported by Google, this is a finding.","discussion":"Google Chrome is being continually updated by the vendor in order to address identified security vulnerabilities. Running an older version of the browser can introduce security vulnerabilities to the system.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42ADF7-6C02-1014-8106-F9F704F1EB21"},{"documentable":"false","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n 2. If the policy \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" is not shown or is not set to false, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"AllowDeletingBrowserHistory\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\",  this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures. Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42B170-6C02-1014-99FD-B98100E1E3BB","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n Policy Name: Enable deleting browser and download history\n Policy State: Disabled\n Policy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Check to make sure that google chrome is set to not allow deletion of browser and download history.)\n","rule_id":"SV-221586r960879","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"rule_version":"DTBC-0052","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221586","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221586","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"rule_title":"Deletion of browser history must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221586r960879_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240052"},"group_id":"V-221586","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-89845","V-75165"],"severity":"medium"},{"group_id_src":"V-221587","reference_identifier":"4081","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0053","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-94633","V-79929"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-221587","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:640053","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Prompt for download location must be enabled.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221587r960879_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-221587","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"false_positives":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42B4C0-6C02-1014-BBF6-C07600CDC9A6","discussion":"If the policy is enabled, the user will be asked where to save each file before downloading. If the policy is disabled, downloads will start immediately, and the user will not be asked where to save the file. If the policy is not configured, the user will be able to change this setting.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome:// policy\n2. If \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"true\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, then this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the \"PromptForDownloadLocation\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"1\", this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Prompt for download location)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path:  Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\n Policy Name: Ask where to save each file before downloading\n Policy State:  Enabled\n Policy Value: N/A","rule_id":"SV-221587r960879"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"rule_id":"SV-221588r1106670","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nWindows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Allow download restrictions\nPolicy State: 1, 2, or 4\nPolicy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DownloadRestrictions is set to 1, 2, 3, or 4)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DownloadRestrictions'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nUniversal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"DownloadRestrictions\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is set to \"0\", this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"DownloadRestrictions\" value name does not exist or its value data is set to \"0\", this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Setting the policy means users cannot bypass download security decisions. There are many types of download warnings within Chrome, which roughly break down into these categories:\n- Malicious, as flagged by the Safe Browsing server.\n- Uncommon or unwanted, as flagged by the Safe Browsing server.\n- A dangerous file type (e.g., all SWF downloads and many EXE downloads).\n\nSetting the policy blocks different subsets of these, depending on its value:\n\n0 = No special restrictions. Default.\n1 = Block malicious downloads and dangerous file types.\n2 = Block malicious downloads, uncommon or unwanted downloads, and dangerous file types.\n3 = Block all downloads.\n4 = Block malicious downloads. Recommended.","uuid":"8E42B824-6C02-1014-B15E-988E6620DA11","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:610055","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221588","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-94635","V-79931"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-221588"},"rule_id_src":"SV-221588r1106670_rule","status":"open","rule_title":"Download restrictions must be configured.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221588","rule_version":"DTBC-0055","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0057","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221590","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","weight":"10.0","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Safe Browsing Extended Reporting must be disabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221590r961083_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221590","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"legacy_ids":["SV-96299","V-81585"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-221590","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:660057","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42BB7D-6C02-1014-9962-D9388E3162E6","check_content":"Universal method:\n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"SafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"SafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\", this is a finding.","discussion":"Enables Google Chrome's Safe Browsing Extended Reporting and prevents users from changing this setting. Extended Reporting sends some system information and page content to Google servers to help detect dangerous apps and sites.\nIf the setting is set to \"True\", then reports will be created and sent whenever necessary (such as when a security interstitial is shown).\nIf the setting is set to \"False\", reports will never be sent.\nIf this policy is set to \"True\" or \"False\", the user will not be able to modify the setting.\nIf this policy is left unset, the user will be able to change the setting and decide whether to send reports or not.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Safe Browsing settings\\\nPolicy Name: Enable Safe Browsing Extended Reporting\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check SafeBrowsingExtendedReportingEnabled value.)\n","rule_id":"SV-221590r961083","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-96301","V-81587"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:670058","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221591","comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"WebUSB must be disabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221591r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221591"},"reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221591","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0058","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n 1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n 2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\n Policy Name: Control use of the WebUSB API\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: 2\n","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (WebUSB must be disabled.)\n","rule_id":"SV-221591r960963","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42BED0-6C02-1014-BA0C-D3B82AD7B8F5","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"DefaultWebUsbGuardSetting\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Allows you to set whether websites are allowed to get access to connected USB devices. Access can be completely blocked, or the user can be asked every time a website wants to get access to connected USB devices.\nIf this policy is left not set, â3â will be used, and the user will be able to change it.\n2 = Do not allow any site to request access to USB devices via the WebUSB API\n3 = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a connected USB device","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false"},{"group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221594","rule_version":"DTBC-0063","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_id":"V-221594","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:520063","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-96311","V-81597"],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221594","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Google Cast must be disabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221594r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"EnableMediaRouter\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"EnableMediaRouter\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\", this is a finding.","discussion":"If this policy is set to âTrueâ or is not set, Google Cast will be enabled, and users will be able to launch it from the app menu, page context menus, media controls on Cast-enabled websites, and (if shown) the âCast toolbarâ icon.\nIf this policy set to âFalseâ, Google Cast will be disabled.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42C23D-6C02-1014-B99A-AC43E14A9FCE","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Google Cast\nPolicy Name: Enable Google Cast\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Google Cast must be disabled.)\n","rule_id":"SV-221594r960963"},{"fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Allow media autoplay\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: N/A","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Autoplay is disabled)\n","rule_id":"SV-221595r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42C6C8-6C02-1014-9341-F2E0C1324A06","check_content":"Universal method: \n 1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n 2. If \"AutoplayAllowed\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the \"AutoplayAllowed\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0\", this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This allows a user to control if videos can play automatically with audio content (without user consent) in Google Chrome.\n\nIf the policy is set to \"True\", Google Chrome is allowed to autoplay media. If the policy is set to \"False\", Google Chrome is not allowed to autoplay media. The \"AutoplayAllowlist\" policy can be used to override this for certain URL patterns. By default, Google Chrome is not allowed to autoplay media. The \"AutoplayAllowlist\" policy can be used to override this for certain URL patterns.","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Autoplay must be disabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221595r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-221595"},"legacy_ids":["SV-96295","V-81581"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:660055","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221595","comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0064","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221595","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0"},{"rule_id_src":"SV-221596r961092_rule","status":"not_reviewed","rule_title":"URLs must be allowlisted for Autoplay use.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-221596"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-96303","V-81589"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:questionnaire:5901"},"group_id":"V-221596","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0065","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221596","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","rule_id":"SV-221596r961092","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\n- Policy Name: Allow media autoplay on a allowlist of URL patterns.\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value 1: [*.]mil\n- Policy Value 2: [*.]gov\n\nNote: Policy values are examples.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-221596, SV-221596r961092, SRG-APP-000210)\n","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"8E42CA3E-6C02-1014-868A-D412CF69EAF1","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar), type chrome://policy.\n2. If âAutoplayAllowlistâ under the âPolicy Nameâ column may be set to a list of administrator-approved URLs under the âPolicy Valueâ column. This requirement is optional.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the âAutoplayAllowlistâ key may contain a list of administrator-approved URLs. This requirement is optional.","discussion":"Controls the allowlist of URL patterns that autoplay will always be enabled on. If the \"AutoplayAllowed\" policy is set to \"True\" then this policy will have no effect. If the \"AutoplayAllowed\" policy is set to \"False\", then any URL patterns set in this policy will still be allowed to play.","mitigations":""},{"weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221597","rule_version":"DTBC-0066","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:690066"},"group_id":"V-221597","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-101303","V-91203"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221597","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"rule_id_src":"SV-221597r961083_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Anonymized data collection must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n2. If \"UrlKeyedAnonymizedDataCollectionEnabled\" is not displayed under the âPolicy Nameâ column or it is not set to \"0\" under the âPolicy Valueâ column, this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the âUrlKeyedAnonymizedDataCollectionEnabled\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0,\" this is a finding.","discussion":"Enable URL-keyed anonymized data collection in Google Chrome and prevent users from changing this setting.\nURL-keyed anonymized data collection sends URLs of pages the user visits to Google to make searches and browsing better.\nIf you enable this policy, URL-keyed anonymized data collection is always active.\nIf you disable this policy, URL-keyed anonymized data collection is never active.\nIf this policy is left not set, URL-keyed anonymized data collection will be enabled but the user will be able to change it.","mitigations":"","uuid":"8E42CD9F-6C02-1014-9062-ABCA500D9D77","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"rule_id":"SV-221597r961083","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable URL-keyed anonymized data collection\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: NA","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable URL-keyed anonymized data collection)\n"},{"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:700067","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-221598","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-101305","V-91205"],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-221598"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Collection of WebRTC event logs must be disabled.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-221598r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-221598","reference_identifier":"4081","rule_version":"DTBC-0067","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable WebRTC event log collection)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Allow collection of WebRTC event logs from Google services\nPolicy State: Disabled\nPolicy Value: NA","rule_id":"SV-221598r961083","discussion":"If the policy is set to âtrueâ, Google Chrome is allowed to collect WebRTC event logs from Google services (e.g., Google Meet), and upload those logs to Google.\nIf the policy is set to âfalseâ, or is unset, Google Chrome may not collect nor upload such logs.\nThese logs contain diagnostic information helpful when debugging issues with audio or video calls in Chrome, such as the time and size of sent and received RTP packets, feedback about congestion on the network, and metadata about time and quality of audio and video frames. These logs do not contain audio or video contents from the call.\nThis data collection by Chrome can only be triggered by Google's web services, such as Google Hangouts or Google Meet.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy\n2. If \"WebRtcEventLogCollectionAllowed\" is not displayed under the âPolicy Nameâ column or it is not set to \"0\" under the âPolicy Valueâ column, this is a finding.\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the \"WebRtcEventLogCollectionAllowed\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"0,\" this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42D0F3-6C02-1014-9A6C-C34132FF0AF4","documentable":"false"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\nPolicy Name: Control where Developer Tools can be used\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Disallow usage of the Developer Tools","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Chrome Developer Tools Availability must be disallowed.)\n","rule_id":"SV-221599r961167","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If the policy \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" is not shown or is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the key \"DeveloperToolsAvailability\" does not exist or is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42D45A-6C02-1014-8D8B-88F8DD265AC8","documentable":"false","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:680062"},"group_id":"V-221599","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-106629","V-97525"],"severity":"low","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-221599","title":"SRG-APP-000266"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Chrome development tools must be disabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-221599r961167_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-221599","rule_version":"DTBC-0068","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"rule_version":"DTBC-0069","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-226401","reference_identifier":"4081","group_tree":{"id":"V-226401","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Guest Mode must be disabled.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-226401r961083_rule","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240069"},"group_id":"V-226401","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-111829","V-102867"],"severity":"medium","documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"If this policy is set to true or not configured, Google Chrome will enable guest logins. Guest logins are Google Chrome profiles where all windows are in incognito mode.\n\nIf this policy is set to false, Google Chrome will not allow guest profiles to be started.","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If BrowserGuestModeEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the BrowserGuestModeEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42D7C0-6C02-1014-A8A8-C72F999A32E9","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable Browser Guest Mode)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable guest mode in browser\nPolicy State: Disabled","rule_id":"SV-226401r961083","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"]},{"rule_id":"SV-226402r961083","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable AutoFill for credit cards\nPolicy State: Disabled","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable auto filling of credit card information)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If AutofillCreditCardEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the AutofillCreditCardEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Enabling Google Chrome's AutoFill feature allows users to auto complete credit card information in web forms using previously stored information.\nIf this setting is disabled, Autofill will never suggest or fill credit card information, nor will it save additional credit card information that the user might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this setting is enabled or has no value, the user will be able to control Autofill for credit cards in the UI.","uuid":"8E42DB00-6C02-1014-814F-9282D882B705","security_override_guidance":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-226402"},"rule_id_src":"SV-226402r961083_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"AutoFill for credit cards must be disabled.","responsibility":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-226402","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240070","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-111831","V-102869"],"rule_version":"DTBC-0070","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-226402"},{"group_id":"V-226403","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240071","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-111833","V-102871"],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-226403"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","rule_title":"AutoFill for addresses must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-226403r961083_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-226403","reference_identifier":"4081","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0071","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable AutoFill for addresses)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Enable AutoFill for addresses\nPolicy State: Disabled","rule_id":"SV-226403r961083","discussion":"Enabling Google Chrome's AutoFill feature allows users to auto complete address information in web forms using previously stored information.\nIf this setting is disabled, Autofill will never suggest or fill address information, nor will it save additional address information that the user might submit while browsing the web.\n\nIf this setting is enabled or has no value, the user will be able to control Autofill for addresses in the UI.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If AutofillAddressEnabled is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the AutofillAddressEnabled value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42DF9C-6C02-1014-A30E-E03AF816A105","documentable":"false"},{"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Disable Browser Guest Mode)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the \"group policy editor\" tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\\nPolicy Name: Import autofill form data from default browser on first run\nPolicy State: Disabled","rule_id":"SV-226404r961083","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42E32A-6C02-1014-BDA6-D20BB3A687EE","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy forces the autofill form data to be imported from the previous default browser if enabled. If enabled, this policy also affects the import dialog.\nIf disabled, the autofill form data is not imported.\n\nIf it is not set, the user may be asked whether to import, or importing may happen automatically.","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If ImportAutofillFormData is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 0 under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n3. If the ImportAutofillFormData value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.\n","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Import AutoFill form data must be disabled.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-226404r961083_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-226404","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-111835","V-102873"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240072"},"group_id":"V-226404","comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0072","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-226404","reference_identifier":"4081","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","weight":"10.0"},{"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:241787"},"group_id":"V-241787","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-34246","V-26961"],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-241787"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-241787r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-241787","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0073","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings\n Policy Name: Control use of the Web Bluetooth API\n Policy State: Enabled\n Policy Value: Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Web Bluetooth API must be disabled.)\n","rule_id":"SV-241787r960963","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type chrome://policy \n2. If DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to 2 under the Policy Value column, then this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n 1. Start regedit\n 2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\n 3. If the DefaultWebBluetoothGuardSetting value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 2, then this is a finding.","discussion":"Setting the policy to 3 lets websites ask for access to nearby Bluetooth devices. Setting the policy to 2 denies access to nearby Bluetooth devices.\n\nLeaving the policy unset lets sites ask for access, but users can change this setting.\n\n2 = Do not allow any site to request access to Bluetooth devices via the Web Bluetooth API\n3 = Allow sites to ask the user to grant access to a nearby Bluetooth device","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42E689-6C02-1014-A594-904AAE0515DE","documentable":"false"},{"mitigations":"","discussion":"QUIC is used by more than half of all connections from the Chrome web browser to Google's servers, and this activity is undesirable in the DoD.\n\nSetting the policy to Enabled or leaving it unset allows the use of QUIC protocol in Google Chrome.\n\nSetting the policy to Disabled disallows the use of QUIC protocol.","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar), type chrome://policy.\n2. If QuicAllowed is not displayed under the Policy Name column or it is not set to False under the Policy Value column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\.\n3. If the QuicAllowed value name does not exist or its value data is not set to 0, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42E9CE-6C02-1014-A11E-FDF9390B23C4","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001762"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Use of the QUIC protocol is disabled)\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the âgroup policy editorâ tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google Chrome.\n- Policy Name: Allow QUIC protocol\n- Policy State: Disabled\n- Policy Value: N/A","rule_id":"SV-245538r961470","group_title":"SRG-APP-000383","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-245538","reference_identifier":"4081","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0074","third_party_tools":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:138"},"group_id":"V-245538","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"id":"V-245538","title":"SRG-APP-000383"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Use of the QUIC protocol must be disabled.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-245538r961470_rule"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc \n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Content Settings.\n- Policy Name: Default cookies setting\n- Policy State: Enabled\n- Policy Value: Keep cookies for the duration of the session","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Session only based cookies are enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultCookiesSetting'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_id":"SV-245539r960864","check_content":"Universal method: \n1. In the omnibox (address bar), type chrome://policy\n2. If the policy \"DefaultCookiesSetting\" is not shown or is not set to \"4\", this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start regedit.\n2. Navigate to HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DefaultCookiesSetting.\n3. If this key does not exist, or is not set to \"4\", this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Cookies must only be allowed per session and only for approved URLs as permanently stored cookies can be used for malicious intent. \n\nApproved URLs may be allowlisted via the CookiesAllowedForUrls policy setting, but is not a requirement.","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42ED06-6C02-1014-8532-F8467605ACBB","documentable":"false","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.chrome:def:240045","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-245539","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-245539","title":"SRG-APP-000080"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Session only based cookies must be enabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-245539r960864_rule","status":"open","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-245539","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0045","third_party_tools":""},{"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275780"},"group_id":"V-275780","comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Create Themes with AI must be disabled.","status":"open","rule_id_src":"SV-275780r1106603_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-275780","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-275780","reference_identifier":"4081","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0075","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Create Themes with AI must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\CreateThemesSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for Create Themes with AI\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow Create Themes","rule_id":"SV-275780r1106603","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"8E42F028-6C02-1014-82CE-95853BA8E692","discussion":"Create Themes with AI lets users create custom themes/wallpapers by preselecting from a list of options.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"CreateThemesSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"CreateThemesSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","documentable":"false"},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0076","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-275781","reference_identifier":"4081","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","status":"open","rule_id_src":"SV-275781r1106671_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"DevTools Generative AI features must be disabled.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-275781"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275781"},"group_id":"V-275781","documentable":"false","uuid":"8E42F376-6C02-1014-82A4-BBEF5639D792","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","discussion":"These features in Google Chrome's DevTools employ generative AI models to provide additional debugging information. To use these features, Google Chrome collects data such as error messages, stack traces, code snippets, and network requests and sends them to a server owned by Google, which runs a generative AI model. Response body or authentication and cookie headers in network requests are not included in the data sent to the server.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"DevToolsGenAiSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"DevToolsGenAiSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-275781r1106671","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (DevTools Generative AI features must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\DevToolsGenAiSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for DevTools Generative AI Features\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow DevTools Generative AI Features","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-275782","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275782","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml"},"rule_id_src":"SV-275782r1106672_rule","status":"open","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"GenAI local foundational model must be disabled.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-275782"},"reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-275782","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0077","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275782r1106672","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for GenAI local foundational model\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not download model","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (GenAI local foundational model must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\GenAILocalFoundationalModelSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","uuid":"8E42FD0E-6C02-1014-B697-9C56041FEC8C","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"GenAILocalFoundationalModelSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"1\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"GenAILocalFoundationalModelSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"1\", this is a finding.","discussion":"Configure how Google Chrome downloads the foundational GenAI model and uses it for inference locally.\n\nWhen the policy is set to Allowed (0) or not set, the model is downloaded automatically, and used for inference.\n\nWhen the policy is set to Disabled (1), the model will not be downloaded.\n\nModel downloading can also be disabled by ComponentUpdatesEnabled.\n\n0 = Downloads model automatically\n1 = Do not download model","mitigations":"","documentable":"false"},{"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275783r1106612","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings forSettings for Help Me Write\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow Help Me Write","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Help Me Write must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\HelpMeWriteSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","uuid":"8E4306AF-6C02-1014-A80A-F977781D6608","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"HelpMeWriteSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"HelpMeWriteSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","discussion":"Help Me Write is an AI-based writing assistant for short-form content on the web. Suggested content is based on prompts entered by the user and the content of the web page.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275783","href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml"},"group_id":"V-275783","rule_id_src":"SV-275783r1106612_rule","status":"open","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Help Me Write must be disabled.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-275783","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-275783","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0078"},{"ccis":["CCI-000169"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275784r1106615","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Settings for AI-powered History Search\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow AI History Search","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (AI-powered History Search must be disabled)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\HistorySearchSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","uuid":"8E430C67-6C02-1014-B4BA-8BBC4C866200","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"HistorySearchSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"HistorySearchSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","discussion":"AI History Search is a feature that allows users to search their browsing history and receive generated answers based on page contents and not just the page title and URL.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-275784","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275784"},"rule_id_src":"SV-275784r1106615_rule","status":"open","rule_title":"AI-powered History Search must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-275784","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"reference_identifier":"4081","group_id_src":"V-275784","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0079"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-275785","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_Google_Chrome_V2R11_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.chrome:def:275785"},"status":"open","rule_id_src":"SV-275785r1106673_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Tab Compare Settings must be disabled.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-275785"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-275785","reference_identifier":"4081","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBC-0080","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-275785r1106673","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:20\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Tab Compare Settings must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\TabCompareSettings'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","fix_text":"Windows group policy:\n1. Open the group policy editor tool with gpedit.msc.\n2. Navigate to Policy Path: Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Google\\Google Chrome\\Generative AI\nPolicy Name: Tab Compare settings\nPolicy State: Enabled\nPolicy Value: Do not allow Tab Compare","uuid":"8E4311E5-6C02-1014-90C4-8F56AFC3D5E5","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"8E414D81-6C02-1014-8FA0-85ECA3A35C0D","discussion":"Tab Compare is an AI-powered tool for comparing information across a user's tabs. For example, the feature can be offered to the user when multiple tabs with products in a similar category are open.\n\n0 = Allow the feature to be used, while allowing Google to use relevant data to improve its AI models. Relevant data may include prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback, depending on the feature. It may also be reviewed by humans to improve AI models. 0 is the default value, except when noted below.\n\n1 = Allow the feature to be used, but does not allow Google to improve models using users' content (including prompts, inputs, outputs, source materials, and written feedback). 1 is the default value for Enterprise users managed by Google Admin console and for Education accounts managed by Google Workspace.\n\n2 = Do not allow the feature.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Universal method:\n1. In the omnibox (address bar) type \"chrome:// policy\".\n2. If \"TabCompareSettings\" is not displayed under the \"Policy Name\" column or it is not set to \"2\" under the \"Policy Value\" column, this is a finding.\n\nWindows method:\n1. Start \"regedit\".\n2. Navigate to \"HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Google\\Chrome\\\".\n3. If the \"TabCompareSettings\" value name does not exist or its value data is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.","documentable":"false"}],"version":"2","size":46,"stig_id":"Google_Chrome_Current_Windows"},{"version":"2","size":137,"stig_id":"IE_11_STIG","release_info":"Release: 6 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","display_name":"Microsoft Internet Explorer 11","stig_name":"Microsoft Internet Explorer 11 Security Technical Implementation Guide","uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","rules":[{"group_id_src":"V-223015","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI015-IE11","mitigation_control":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59339","V-46475"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:421"},"group_id":"V-223015","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223015r961863_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"The Internet Explorer warning about certificate address mismatch must be enforced.","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223015"},"false_positives":"","uuid":"95C171EE-6C02-1014-AD7E-93853AE411C0","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"This parameter warns users if the certificate being presented by the website is invalid. Since server certificates are used to validate the identity of the web server it is critical to warn the user of a potential issue with the certificate being presented by the web server. This setting aids to prevent spoofing attacks.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page 'Turn on certificate address mismatch warning' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"WarnOnBadCertRecving\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223015r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Security Page/Turn on certificate address mismatch warning)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page 'Turn on certificate address mismatch warning' to 'Enabled'.  "},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI018-IE11","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-223016","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","weight":"10.0","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Check for publishers certificate revocation must be enforced.","status":"open","rule_id_src":"SV-223016r961038_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-223016"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59341","V-46477"],"severity":"low","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223016","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml"},"group_id":"V-223016","comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C178E5-6C02-1014-9EC9-83A83FCE5109","mitigations":"","discussion":"Check for publisher's certificate revocation options should be enforced to ensure all PKI signed objects are validated.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nOpen Internet Explorer.\nFrom the menu bar, select \"Tools\".\nFrom the \"Tools\" drop-down menu, select \"Internet Options\". From the \"Internet Options\" window, select the \"Advanced\" tab, from the \"Advanced\" tab window, scroll down to the \"Security\" category, and verify the \"Check for publisher's certificate revocation\" box is selected.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n HKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing Criteria\n\nIf the value \"State\" is \"REG_DWORD = 23C00\", this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Check for publishers certificate revocation must be enforced.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing\\State'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nOpen Internet Explorer.\nFrom the menu bar, select \"Tools\".\nFrom the \"Tools\" drop-down menu, select \"Internet Options\". From the \"Internet Options\" window, select the \"Advanced\" tab from the \"Advanced\" tab window, scroll down to the \"Security\" category, and select the \"Check for publisher's certificate revocation\" box.\n\nNote: Manual entry in the registry key:\n\nHKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\Current Version\\WinTrust\\Trust Providers\\Software Publishing for the value \"State\", set to \"REG_DWORD = 23C00\", may first be required.","rule_id":"SV-223016r961038","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"uuid":"95C17D63-6C02-1014-8E06-EAB58C9FEF63","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"Active X controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. This policy setting allows you to manage whether users may download signed ActiveX controls from a page in the zone. If you enable this policy, users can download signed controls without user intervention. If you select Prompt in the drop-down box, users are queried whether to download controls signed by untrusted publishers. Code signed by trusted publishers is silently downloaded. If you disable the policy setting, signed controls cannot be downloaded.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223017r961089","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Download signed ActiveX controls)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","group_id_src":"V-223017","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI022-IE11","mitigation_control":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59345","V-46481"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223017","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:422","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223017r961089_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_tree":{"id":"V-223017","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"false_positives":""},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Download unsigned ActiveX controls)\n","rule_id":"SV-223018r961089","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. This policy setting allows you to manage whether users may download unsigned ActiveX controls from the zone. If you enable this policy setting, users can run unsigned controls without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow the unsigned control to run. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot run unsigned controls. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot run unsigned controls.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C1817B-6C02-1014-9CA6-88942B1569A6","documentable":"false","group_id":"V-223018","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:423","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59347","V-46483"],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223018"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223018r961089_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223018","rule_version":"DTBI023-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59365","V-46501"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:424","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223019","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223019r961092_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223019","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223019","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI024-IE11","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223019r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","uuid":"95C1855C-6C02-1014-AAB0-F43524529229","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false"},{"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Java permissions)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","rule_id":"SV-223020r960963","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C1893A-6C02-1014-A602-D3CF8609DB64","group_tree":{"id":"V-223020","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Java permissions must be disallowed (Internet zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223020r960963_rule","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:426","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223020","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59371","V-46507"],"severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI031-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223020","reference_identifier":"4095"},{"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Access data sources across domains)\n","rule_id":"SV-223021r1117169","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C18D07-6C02-1014-8A2E-8AD91A779C53","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. Access to data sources across multiple domains must be controlled based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223021r1117169_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223021","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"legacy_ids":["SV-59373","V-46509"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223021","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:427","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI032-IE11","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223021","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","weight":"10.0"},{"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C192F0-6C02-1014-87F0-E516761AA538","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value for \"1802\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Internet zone are likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files)\n","rule_id":"SV-223022r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI036-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223022","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223022r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223022"},"legacy_ids":["SV-59375","V-46511"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:428","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223022","comments":null},{"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223023r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_tree":{"id":"V-223023","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59377","V-46513"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:429"},"group_id":"V-223023","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI038-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223023","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","rule_id":"SV-223023r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Launching applications and files in an IFRAME)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C19826-6C02-1014-89C9-9119AC6B3AB3","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding."},{"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223024r1117169_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223024"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59379","V-46515"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223024","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:430","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI039-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223024","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","rule_id":"SV-223024r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Navigate windows and frames across different domains)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C19D29-6C02-1014-A510-D21BA493D370","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"Frames that navigate across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\InternetSettings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding."},{"rule_version":"DTBI042-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","group_id_src":"V-223025","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000231","id":"V-223025"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223025r961128_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Internet zone).","potential_impacts":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:431","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223025","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59381","V-46517"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. It is possible for sites hosting malicious content to exploit this feature as part of an attack against visitors browsing the site. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured. ","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C1A4A0-6C02-1014-BA31-F68F68F94B8B","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-223025r961128","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Userdata persistence)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001199"]},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI044-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223026","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223026r960963_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223026"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59385","V-46521"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223026","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:432","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C1AE15-6C02-1014-A9A1-9C276E7AC326","mitigations":"","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow cut, copy, or paste operations from the clipboard via script)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223026r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59387","V-46523"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223027","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:433"},"comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured to prompt (Internet zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223027r1043178_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-223027","title":"SRG-APP-000219"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223027","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI046-IE11","ccis":["CCI-001184"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Logon options)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt for user name and password' from the drop-down box.  ","rule_id":"SV-223027r1043178","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C1B6A6-6C02-1014-A3CF-F18E45E91D50","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. âAnonymous logonâ disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. âPrompt for user name and passwordâ queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon with current user name and passwordâ attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. The most secure option is to configure this setting to âEnabledâ; âAnonymous logonâ, but configuring this setting to âEnabledâ; âPrompt for user name and passwordâ, provides a reasonable balance between security and usability.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt for user name and password' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536 (decimal), this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","documentable":"false"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223028r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'High Safety' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Intranet Zone\\Java permissions)\n","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'High Safety' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536, (Decimal), this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","uuid":"95C1BB8B-6C02-1014-9CF8-CED0EC35907E","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223028","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:434","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59389","V-46525"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223028","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223028r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Intranet zone).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223028","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI061-IE11","third_party_tools":""},{"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223029","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI062-IE11","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59865","V-46999"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223029","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:566"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223029r961086_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Intranet zone.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223029","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"uuid":"95C1BF88-6C02-1014-B6CF-DE41B26D39D9","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Intranet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223029r961086","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Intranet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Intranet Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n"},{"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'High Safety' from the drop-down box.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Trusted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","rule_id":"SV-223030r960963","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"documentable":"false","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'High Safety' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 65536, (Decimal), this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C1C343-6C02-1014-A403-D515B358B736","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223030"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be configured with High Safety (Trusted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223030r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-223030","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:435"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59407","V-46543"],"severity":"medium","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI091-IE11","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223030"},{"uuid":"95C1C6DF-6C02-1014-8C31-C9D3D81E7A9B","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Trusted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223031r961086","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Trusted Sites Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Trusted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","group_id_src":"V-223031","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI092-IE11","mitigation_control":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59875","V-47009"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223031","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:569","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223031r961086_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Trusted Sites zone.","group_tree":{"id":"V-223031","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"false_positives":""},{"rule_id":"SV-223032r1117169","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C1CA6A-6C02-1014-A477-DEFC668BFA02","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2708\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223032r1117169_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223032"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59409","V-46545"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:549","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223032","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI1000-IE11","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-223032","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039"},{"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C1CE03-6C02-1014-88A2-9AE8F9B5A3CB","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you enable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223033r1117169","group_id_src":"V-223033","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1005-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59411","V-46547"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223033","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:548","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223033r1117169_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223033"},"false_positives":""},{"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C1D1CD-6C02-1014-B6DB-C6D83577B15D","mitigations":"","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict ActiveX Install\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_id":"SV-223034r960921","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI1010-IE11","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-223034","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","weight":"10.0","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Explorer).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223034r960921_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-223034"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59413","V-46549"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:535","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223034","comments":null},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"rule_id":"SV-223035r960921","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict ActiveX Install\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C1D55A-6C02-1014-B6F3-DB9209F64152","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223035","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:536","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59417","V-46553"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000112","id":"V-223035"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223035r960921_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (iexplore).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223035","rule_version":"DTBI1020-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223036","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1025-IE11","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223036","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:550","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59419","V-46555"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223036","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223036r1117169_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2708\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users cannot change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in the same window. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","uuid":"95C1D8F1-6C02-1014-8596-D387611B9C4A","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"rule_id":"SV-223036r1117169","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Security Page/Restricted Sites Zone/Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window)\n"},{"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","rule_id":"SV-223037r961086","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C1DCBE-6C02-1014-9F5F-C8522589D374","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false","legacy_ids":["SV-59863","V-46997"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:565"},"group_id":"V-223037","comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Internet zone.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223037r961086_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223037"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223037","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1046-IE11"},{"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223038","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:568"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59871","V-47005"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223038","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223038r961086_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Restricted Sites zone.","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223038","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1051-IE11","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"rule_id":"SV-223038r961086","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C1E08D-6C02-1014-A99C-89CB9B5FD2D7","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"ccis":["CCI-001242"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223039r961194","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverride is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","uuid":"95C1E4B2-6C02-1014-8A0A-99C8D4777324","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverride\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter prevents the user from browsing to or downloading from sites that are known to host malicious content. SmartScreen Filter also prevents the execution of files that are known to be malicious. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79201","V-64711"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223039","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:578"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223039r961194_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings must be enabled.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-223039"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223039","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1060-IE11"},{"uuid":"95C1E8D6-6C02-1014-997D-AE4489D6155A","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter.\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter warns the user about executable files that Internet Explorer users do not commonly download from the internet. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223040r961089","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ to âEnabledâ.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223040","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI1065-IE11","mitigation_control":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79203","V-64713"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:572"},"group_id":"V-223040","rule_id_src":"SV-223040r961089_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet must be enabled.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223040","title":"SRG-APP-000209"}},{"rule_version":"DTBI1070-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223041","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223041"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls must be enabled.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223041r961092_rule","group_id":"V-223041","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:574"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-79205","V-64715"],"severity":"medium","documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to prevent the installation of ActiveX controls on a per-user basis. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls cannot be installed on a per-user basis. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, ActiveX controls can be installed on a per-user basis.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C1ED30-6C02-1014-8E59-E6CB5E5CDD37","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX\\BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","rule_id":"SV-223041r961092","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001170"]},{"uuid":"95C1F1A4-6C02-1014-A5DB-EA4FCACE9CBD","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting prevents the user from ignoring Secure Sockets Layer/Transport Layer Security (SSL/TLS) certificate errors that interrupt browsing (such as âexpiredâ, ârevokedâ, or âname mismatchâ errors) in Internet Explorer. If you enable this policy setting, the user cannot continue browsing. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose to ignore certificate errors and continue browsing.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventIgnoreCertErrors\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001954"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223042r961596","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\PreventIgnoreCertErrors is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ to âEnabledâ.   ","group_id_src":"V-223042","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000427","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1075-IE11","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79207","V-64717"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223042","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:575","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223042r961596_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Prevent ignoring certificate errors option must be enabled.","group_tree":{"id":"V-223042","title":"SRG-APP-000427"},"false_positives":""},{"ccis":["CCI-001242"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223043r961194","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   ","uuid":"95C1FAEA-6C02-1014-9E0A-AC2232E7A84C","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79209","V-64719"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:577","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223043","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223043r961194_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Internet Zone must be enabled.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000278","id":"V-223043"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223043","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI1080-IE11","mitigation_control":""},{"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1085-IE11","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223044","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223044","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223044r961194_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Restricted Sites Zone must be enabled.","responsibility":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:576"},"group_id":"V-223044","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79211","V-64721"],"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C20161-6C02-1014-968C-AC351855D3C2","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-223044r961194","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001242"]},{"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C20F35-6C02-1014-B246-9B13F2E131DB","mitigations":"","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223045r961092","group_id_src":"V-223045","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1090-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-79213","V-64723"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223045","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:579"},"comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Intranet Zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223045r961092_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-223045","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"false_positives":""},{"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1095-IE11","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223046","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223046"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223046r961092_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Trusted Sites Zone).","responsibility":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:573","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223046","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79215","V-64725"],"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C21A76-6C02-1014-9603-AFC37ADBC92A","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-223046r961092","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001170"]},{"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C22872-6C02-1014-B1FE-83503CA580E5","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","mitigations":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" is set to âEnabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"RunThisTimeEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\RunThisTimeEnabled is set to 0)\n","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" to \"Enabled\".","rule_id":"SV-223048r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI1105-IE11","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-223048","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Run once selection for running outdated ActiveX controls must be disabled.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223048r960963_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-223048","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-87395","V-72757"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:585"},"group_id":"V-223048","comments":null},{"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223049r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\VersionCheckEnabled is set to 1)\n","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" to \"Disabled\".","uuid":"95C232D8-6C02-1014-84A8-B5E6CDCA8F4F","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" is set to âDisabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"VersionCheckEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-87397","V-72759"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223049","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:586","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223049r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Enabling outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer must be blocked.","group_tree":{"id":"V-223049","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223049","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI1110-IE11","mitigation_control":""},{"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:583"},"group_id":"V-223050","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-87399","V-72761"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223050","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223050r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Internet Zone.","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id_src":"V-223050","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_version":"DTBI1115-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223050r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Pane &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users will not be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C23CED-6C02-1014-A446-AF1B1191E188","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223051","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI112-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59437","V-46573"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:436","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223051","comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223051r961089_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000209","id":"V-223051"},"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2455D-6C02-1014-9C4A-F32BC1A0CAFB","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download signed ActiveX controls)\n","rule_id":"SV-223051r961089"},{"stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users wonât be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C24D01-6C02-1014-9697-F6202BC5DE8C","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223052r960963","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ.\n\nIn the Options windows, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.\n \n","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223052","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1120-IE11","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:584"},"group_id":"V-223052","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-87401","V-72763"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223052"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223052r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Restricted Sites Zone.","responsibility":""},{"group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223053","rule_version":"DTBI1125-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:588"},"group_id":"V-223053","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-89849","V-75169"],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223053","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Internet zone).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223053r961089_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C254B9-6C02-1014-8BD3-BBEE0152D9FB","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","rule_id":"SV-223053r961089"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59439","V-46575"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223054","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:437"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223054r961089_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223054","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223054","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI113-IE11","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223054r961089","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download unsigned ActiveX controls)\n","uuid":"95C25C42-6C02-1014-9E21-CFEBFDE9443D","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. They must also be digitally signed.","documentable":"false"},{"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223055r961089_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223055","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"legacy_ids":["SV-89851","V-75171"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223055","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:589","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI1130-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223055","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","weight":"10.0","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone-&gt;'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","rule_id":"SV-223055r961089","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C26385-6C02-1014-B5E3-F814A94CCB2B","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":""},{"group_id":"V-223056","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:591","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-106631","V-97527"],"severity":"low","group_tree":{"id":"V-223056","title":"SRG-APP-000266"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Development Tools Must Be Disabled.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223056r961167_rule","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223056","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_version":"DTBI1135-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Developer Tools are disabled)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ to âEnabledâ.","rule_id":"SV-223056r961167","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ must be âEnabledâ. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKEY_LOCAL_Machine\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\IEDevTools\nCriteria: If the value \"Disabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C26AB7-6C02-1014-948A-D4FB97A49B59","documentable":"false"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"rule_id":"SV-223057r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"ActiveX controls not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C271E6-6C02-1014-9100-F3F0B38420A7","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223057","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:438","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59441","V-46577"],"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223057"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223057r961092_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id_src":"V-223057","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_version":"DTBI114-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether ActiveX controls and plug-ins can be run on pages from the specified zone. ActiveX controls not marked as safe should not be executed. If you enable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins can run without user intervention. If you disable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins are prevented from running.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C27917-6C02-1014-B3D0-F983CC315061","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run ActiveX controls and plugins)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223058r961863","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223058","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_version":"DTBI115-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_id":"V-223058","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:439"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59443","V-46579"],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223058"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"ActiveX controls and plug-ins must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223058r961863_rule"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"rule_id":"SV-223059r961092","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting)\n","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1405\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting allows management of whether ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting can interact with a script. If you enable this policy setting, script interaction can occur automatically without user intervention. ActiveX controls not marked as safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C27FEB-6C02-1014-9E75-BBB5DF5EB4B8","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:440"},"group_id":"V-223059","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59445","V-46581"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223059"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223059r961092_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223059","rule_version":"DTBI116-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C28A8E-6C02-1014-9233-99BBFBBC5F8B","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1803\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Sites located in the Restricted Sites Zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore downloads from this zone should be blocked. Files should not be able to be downloaded from sites that are considered restricted. This policy setting allows you to manage whether file downloads are permitted from the zone. This option is determined by the zone of the page with the link causing the download, not the zone from which the file is delivered.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow file downloads)\n","rule_id":"SV-223060r960963","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223060","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI119-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59447","V-46583"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223060","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:441"},"comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"File downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223060r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223060"}},{"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223061","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI121-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59451","V-46587"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223061","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:453"},"comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223061r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223061","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C29242-6C02-1014-9525-8A2530F05003","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","rule_id":"SV-223061r960963"},{"rule_version":"DTBI122-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223062","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223062"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223062r1117169_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223062","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:443"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59453","V-46589"],"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","uuid":"95C2981C-6C02-1014-8640-E334B1BB586C","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-223062r1117169","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Access data sources across domains)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001414"]},{"rule_version":"DTBI123-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223063","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223063"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Allow META REFRESH property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223063r961863_rule","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:444","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223063","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59455","V-46591"],"severity":"medium","documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"It is possible that users will unknowingly be redirected to a site hosting malicious content. 'Allow META REFRESH' must have a level of protection based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether a user's browser can be redirected to another web page if the author of the web page uses the Meta Refresh setting to redirect browsers to another web page.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1608\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C29C55-6C02-1014-87CD-EA38F75FE7F7","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow META REFRESH)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","rule_id":"SV-223063r961863","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"]},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223064r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Restricted Sites zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1802\" is REG_DWORD=3, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C2A03F-6C02-1014-BC7E-AFA048564E84","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:445","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223064","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59457","V-46593"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223064","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223064r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id_src":"V-223064","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_version":"DTBI126-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223065r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching applications and files in an IFRAME)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C2A41D-6C02-1014-8A91-8264B2F0A867","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223065","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:447","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59461","V-46597"],"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223065"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223065r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id_src":"V-223065","reference_identifier":"4095","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI128-IE11","third_party_tools":""},{"rule_version":"DTBI129-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223066","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223066","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223066r1117169_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-223066","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:448"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59463","V-46599"],"severity":"medium","documentable":"false","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Frames navigating across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2A7BF-6C02-1014-9352-A44847A37E3C","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Navigate windows and frames across different domains)\n","rule_id":"SV-223066r1117169","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001414"]},{"rule_id":"SV-223067r961128","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Userdata persistence)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C2AD81-6C02-1014-B9D0-954DC1E84415","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223067r961128_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000231","id":"V-223067"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59465","V-46601"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223067","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:449","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI132-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223067","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231"},{"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1400\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Active scripts hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. Active scripting must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script code on pages in the zone are run.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C2B1B6-6C02-1014-B707-D73251887F21","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-223068r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow active scripting)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_version":"DTBI133-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223068","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223068","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223068r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Active scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites Zone).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:450","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223068","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59467","V-46603"]},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59469","V-46605"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223069","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:451","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223069r960963_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223069"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223069","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI134-IE11","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow cut, copy, or paste operations from the clipboard via script)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_id":"SV-223069r960963","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2B635-6C02-1014-9480-B4FB6B154D14","mitigations":"","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","documentable":"false"},{"documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. âAnonymous logonâ disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. âPrompt for user name and passwordâ queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon with current user name and passwordâ attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. The most secure option is to configure this setting to âEnabledâ; âAnonymous logonâ. This will prevent users from submitting credentials to servers in this security zone.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Anonymous logon' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 196608 (decimal), this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2BA7E-6C02-1014-8726-C792538D3E90","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Logon options)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Anonymous logon' from the drop-down box.","rule_id":"SV-223070r1043178","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001184"],"rule_version":"DTBI136-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223070","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"id":"V-223070","title":"SRG-APP-000219"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured and enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223070r1043178_rule","group_id":"V-223070","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:452"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59471","V-46607"],"severity":"medium"},{"rule_id":"SV-223071r960879","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Disable Configuring History must be Enabled)\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\40 entered in Days to keep pages in History)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' to 'Enabled', and enter '40' in 'Days to keep pages in History'.","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C2BEBE-6C02-1014-AEB3-F293193B896D","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"This setting specifies the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The delete Browsing History option can be accessed using Tools, Internet Options, \"General\" tab, and then click Settings under Browsing History. If you enable this policy setting, a user cannot set the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List must be specified. Users will not be able to delete browsing history. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, a user can set the number of days that Internet Explorer tracks views of pages in the History List. Users can delete browsing history.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' must be 'Enabled', and '40' entered in 'Days to keep pages in History'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Control Panel Criteria: If the value \"History\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding. AND  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Url History Criteria: If the value \"DaysToKeep\" is REG_DWORD = 40 (decimal), this is not a finding.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223071r960879_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Configuring History setting must be set to 40 days.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-223071"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59473","V-46609"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:513"},"group_id":"V-223071","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI300-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223071","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59479","V-46615"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:419","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223072","rule_id_src":"SV-223072r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be set to disallow users to add/delete sites.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223072","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223072","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI318-IE11","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223072r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' to 'Enabled'.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Add/Delete Sites)\n","uuid":"95C2C31F-6C02-1014-9780-AC8944BBE7E0","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_zones_map_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This setting prevents users from adding sites to various security zones. Users should not be able to add sites to different zones, as this could allow them to bypass security controls of the system. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will be able to add or remove sites from the Trusted Sites and Restricted Sites zones at will and change settings in the Local Intranet zone. This configuration could allow sites that host malicious mobile code to be added to these zones, and users could execute the code.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false"},{"group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223073","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI319-IE11","third_party_tools":"","group_id":"V-223073","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:418"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59481","V-46617"],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223073","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to disallow users to change policies.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223073r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_options_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting prevents users from changing the Internet Explorer policies on the machine. Policy changes should be made by administrators only, so this setting should be enabled. If you enable this policy setting, you disable the \"Custom level\" button and \"Security\" level for this zone slider on the Security tab in the Internet Options dialog box. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users will be able to change the settings for security zones. It prevents users from changing security zone policy settings that are established by the administrator.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2C6EB-6C02-1014-A4ED-FE215A9309E2","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Change Policies)\n","rule_id":"SV-223073r961863"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223074","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI320-IE11","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59483","V-46619"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:417"},"group_id":"V-223074","comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to use machine settings.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223074r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223074"},"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2CAC3-6C02-1014-B299-834E4B603DD5","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_HKLM_only\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting enforces consistent security zone settings to all users of the computer. Security zones control browser behavior at various websites and it is desirable to maintain a consistent policy for all users of a machine. This policy setting affects how security zone changes apply to different users. If you enable this policy setting, changes that one user makes to a security zone will apply to all users of that computer. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of the same computer are allowed to establish their own security zone settings.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' to 'Enabled'. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Use Only Machine Settings)\n","rule_id":"SV-223074r961863"},{"rule_title":"Security checking features must be enforced.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223075r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223075","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"legacy_ids":["SV-59485","V-46621"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:457","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223075","comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI325-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223075","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","weight":"10.0","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' to 'Disabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn off the Security Settings Check feature)\n","rule_id":"SV-223075r961863","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2D155-6C02-1014-BF6E-F2E1F4E700C5","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security Criteria: If the value \"DisableSecuritySettingsCheck\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting turns off the Security Settings Check feature, which checks Internet Explorer security settings to determine when the settings put Internet Explorer at risk. If you enable this policy setting, the security settings check will not be performed. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the security settings check will be performed.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":""},{"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"Microsoft ActiveX controls and file downloads often have digital signatures attached that certify the file's integrity and the identity of the signer (creator) of the software. Such signatures help ensure unmodified software is downloaded and the user can positively identify the signer to determine whether you trust them enough to run their software.","check_content":"Note: Some legitimate software and controls may have an invalid signature. You should carefully test such software in isolation before it is allowed to be used on an organization's network.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"RunInvalidSignatures\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C2D550-6C02-1014-B054-B226C3891551","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-223076r961092","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Allow Software to Run or Install Even if the Signature is Invalid)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' to 'Disabled'. ","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI350-IE11","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","group_id_src":"V-223076","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"id":"V-223076","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223076r961092_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Software must be disallowed to run or install with invalid signatures.","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:459"},"group_id":"V-223076","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59489","V-46625"]},{"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows)\n","rule_id":"SV-223077r961131","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"documentable":"false","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Isolation64Bit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer 11 uses 64-bit processes (for greater security) or 32-bit processes (for greater compatibility) when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows.Important: Some ActiveX controls and toolbars may not be available when 64-bit processes are used. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 32-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you don't configure this policy setting, users can turn this feature on or off using Internet Explorer settings. This feature is turned off by default.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2D93F-6C02-1014-ACA7-F446B7DA2E1D","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000233","id":"V-223077"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The 64-bit tab processes, when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows, must be turned on.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223077r961131_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:564"},"group_id":"V-223077","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59861","V-46995"],"severity":"medium","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI356-IE11","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223077"},{"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Server Certificate Revocation)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_id":"SV-223078r961038","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"documentable":"false","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer will check revocation status of servers' certificates. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check to see if server certificates have been revoked. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"CertificateRevocation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2DDEC-6C02-1014-8B0C-E7633A1E3076","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000175","id":"V-223078"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Checking for server certificate revocation must be enforced.","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223078r961038_rule","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:461","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223078","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59493","V-46629"],"severity":"low","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI365-IE11","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223078","reference_identifier":"4095"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59497","V-46633"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223079","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:462","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223079r960954_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Checking for signatures on downloaded programs must be enforced.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000131","id":"V-223079"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223079","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI370-IE11","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001749"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223079r960954","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Signature on Downloaded Programs)\n","uuid":"95C2E236-6C02-1014-B46D-CDC4BD24DB08","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"CheckExeSignatures\" is REG_SZ = yes, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer checks for digital signatures (which identifies the publisher of signed software and verifies it has not been modified or tampered with) on user computers before downloading executable programs. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check the digital signatures of executable programs and display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you do not configure this policy, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers.","documentable":"false"},{"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI375-IE11","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223080","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223080","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"All network paths (UNCs) for Intranet sites must be disallowed.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223080r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:463"},"group_id":"V-223080","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59499","V-46635"],"severity":"medium","documentable":"false","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\ZoneMap Criteria: If the value \"UNCAsIntranet\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Some UNC paths could refer to servers not managed by the organization, which means they could host malicious content; and therefore, it is safest to not include all UNC paths in the Intranet Sites zone. This policy setting controls whether URLs representing UNCs are mapped into the local Intranet security zone. If you enable this policy setting, all network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone. If you disable this policy setting, network paths are not necessarily mapped into the Intranet Zone (other rules might map one there). If you do not configure this policy setting, users choose whether network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2EBCF-6C02-1014-AE89-CB8A66BE003F","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' to 'Disabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs))\n","rule_id":"SV-223080r961863","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"]},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59501","V-46637"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:464"},"group_id":"V-223081","comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Internet zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223081r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223081","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223081","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI385-IE11","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\n","rule_id":"SV-223081r960963","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2F174-6C02-1014-91A7-8B49741425E5","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false"},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI390-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223082","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223082r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223082","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"legacy_ids":["SV-59503","V-46639"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223082","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:465","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2F5A4-6C02-1014-9768-9712D6666903","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\n","rule_id":"SV-223082r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2F9B5-6C02-1014-8E89-B00F6EABA5B5","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","rule_id":"SV-223083r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI395-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223083","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Internet zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223083r960963_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223083"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59505","V-46641"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223083","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:466","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI415-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223084","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Internet zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223084r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223084","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"legacy_ids":["SV-59507","V-46643"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223084","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:467","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C2FDAF-6C02-1014-8EEB-89431D6ED4B4","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\n","rule_id":"SV-223084r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223085","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI425-IE11","mitigation_control":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59509","V-46645"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:468","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223085","rule_id_src":"SV-223085r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Local Machine zone).","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223085","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"uuid":"95C301AF-6C02-1014-9FA1-AD34E4B5266E","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.  ","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223085r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\n"},{"ccis":["CCI-001662"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223086r961086","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   ","uuid":"95C3058F-6C02-1014-AE5E-F9E09F8FC61F","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt;Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59869","V-47003"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:567"},"group_id":"V-223086","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223086r961086_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Local Machine zone.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000207","id":"V-223086"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223086","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI426-IE11"},{"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223087r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","uuid":"95C30975-6C02-1014-9C38-8A323043F934","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59511","V-46647"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223087","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:469","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223087r960963_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Local Machine zone).","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223087"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223087","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI430-IE11"},{"rule_id":"SV-223088r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Intranet Zone\\Java permissions)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C3149E-6C02-1014-AE67-C23496C60E1A","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value\" 1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223088r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Intranet zone).","group_tree":{"id":"V-223088","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59513","V-46649"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223088","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:470","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI435-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223088","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141"},{"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI440-IE11","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id_src":"V-223089","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223089"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223089r960963_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Trusted Sites zone).","potential_impacts":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223089","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:471"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59517","V-46653"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C32B38-6C02-1014-A6D9-BF4D39AFEB8B","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-223089r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Trusted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   ","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"]},{"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223090"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223090r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223090","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:473","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59527","V-46663"],"rule_version":"DTBI450-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223090","rule_id":"SV-223090r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C330BD-6C02-1014-A9F4-95041F0AC557","security_override_guidance":""},{"documentable":"false","uuid":"95C334CB-6C02-1014-AF00-902E8FC88ED5","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223091r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Loose or un-compiled XAML files)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI455-IE11","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-223091","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223091r961863_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223091"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59529","V-46665"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223091","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:474"}},{"weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","group_id_src":"V-223092","reference_identifier":"4095","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI460-IE11","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:475"},"group_id":"V-223092","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59533","V-46669"],"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223092"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223092r961863_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C33891-6C02-1014-B9B5-BFFE7B72DDDE","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"rule_id":"SV-223092r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Loose XAML files)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI485-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223093","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","weight":"10.0","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Internet zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223093r961131_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-223093","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59545","V-46681"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:480"},"group_id":"V-223093","comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C33C81-6C02-1014-BD38-C23F4BEBCEC9","mitigations":"","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223093r961131","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C34034-6C02-1014-B43D-BE4BDE41837B","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled' and select 'Enable', from the drop-down box.  ","rule_id":"SV-223094r961131","group_id_src":"V-223094","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI490-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59549","V-46685"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:481"},"group_id":"V-223094","comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223094r961131_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-223094","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"false_positives":""},{"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.  ","rule_id":"SV-223095r960963","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"documentable":"false","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3443D-6C02-1014-8532-E373DDD19A29","group_tree":{"id":"V-223095","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Internet zone).","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223095r960963_rule","group_id":"V-223095","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:482"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59553","V-46689"],"severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI495-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223095","reference_identifier":"4095"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59555","V-46691"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:483","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223096","rule_id_src":"SV-223096r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223096"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223096","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI500-IE11","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223096r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\n","uuid":"95C347FF-6C02-1014-803A-DE755F46A559","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false"},{"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C34BFF-6C02-1014-959F-D02E4CF1D69A","discussion":"This policy setting allows a user to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Internet zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If \"Prompt\" is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223097r1117169","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI515-IE11","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-223097","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","weight":"10.0","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Internet zone.","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223097r1117169_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223097"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59557","V-46693"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:484","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223097","comments":null},{"ccis":["CCI-001414"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223098r1117169","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\n","uuid":"95C35035-6C02-1014-9167-B93B0478E293","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Restricted zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If Prompt is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59559","V-46695"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223098","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:485","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223098r1117169_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Restricted Sites zone.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223098","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223098","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI520-IE11","mitigation_control":""},{"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223099","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:486","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59565","V-46701"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223099","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223099r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Allow binary and script behaviors must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223099","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI575-IE11","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223099r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow binary and script behaviors)\n","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2000\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage dynamic binary and script behaviors of components that encapsulate specific functionality for HTML elements, to which they were attached. If you enable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.   If you select \"Administrator approved\" in the drop-down box, only the behaviors listed in the Admin-approved Behaviors under Binary Behaviors Security Restriction policy are available.    If you disable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are not available unless applications have implemented a custom security manager. If you do not configure this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C3546C-6C02-1014-BBD4-84CDF84C1AFA","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223100r960963","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C35898-6C02-1014-AE2C-E7A0694316A4","group_tree":{"id":"V-223100","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223100r960963_rule","group_id":"V-223100","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:487","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59569","V-46705"],"severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI580-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223100","reference_identifier":"4095"},{"uuid":"95C35D73-6C02-1014-A17B-AF67B37CA146","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting your network.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223101r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","group_id_src":"V-223101","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI590-IE11","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59573","V-46709"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:488"},"group_id":"V-223101","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223101r961083_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced. (Reserved)","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223101"},"false_positives":""},{"rule_version":"DTBI592-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223102","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223102"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (Explorer).","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223102r961083_rule","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:502"},"group_id":"V-223102","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59575","V-46711"],"severity":"medium","documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to the organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C36239-6C02-1014-8AFC-C8837C945508","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_id":"SV-223102r961083","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"]},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59577","V-46713"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:503","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223103","comments":null,"rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (iexplore).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223103r961083_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223103"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223103","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI594-IE11","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","rule_id":"SV-223103r961083","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3671F-6C02-1014-9CDF-8B291C3E5525","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates that the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure that executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false"},{"rule_version":"DTBI595-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","group_id_src":"V-223104","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"id":"V-223104","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223104r961083_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Reserved).","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223104","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:489"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59579","V-46715"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends you configure this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C36CA7-6C02-1014-B1F7-F8E32412E2F8","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-223104r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"]},{"group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223105","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_version":"DTBI596-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_id":"V-223105","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:510"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59581","V-46717"],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223105"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Explorer).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223105r961083_rule","mitigations":"","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C372D9-6C02-1014-B09A-8D8387FA4CEC","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","rule_id":"SV-223105r961083"},{"documentable":"false","uuid":"95C3770E-6C02-1014-A061-8C66E8A9883A","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223106r961083","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI597-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223106","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223106r961083_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (iexplore).","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223106"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59583","V-46719"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223106","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:511"}},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59585","V-46721"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223107","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:504"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223107r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Reserved).","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223107","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223107","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI599-IE11","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223107r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","uuid":"95C37DFD-6C02-1014-9DAB-814D23F0FEB5","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","documentable":"false"},{"group_tree":{"id":"V-223108","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223108r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Explorer).","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:490","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223108","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59587","V-46723"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI600-IE11","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id_src":"V-223108","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_id":"SV-223108r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C382BA-6C02-1014-90DF-B30771A2F1DE","security_override_guidance":""},{"uuid":"95C386B3-6C02-1014-833D-B02B2B378AC6","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223109r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","group_id_src":"V-223109","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI605-IE11","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59589","V-46725"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223109","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:491"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223109r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (iexplore).","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223109"},"false_positives":""},{"documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C38A8A-6C02-1014-A0A3-EBB9EE52FA70","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_id":"SV-223110r961131","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI610-IE11","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223110","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"id":"V-223110","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Reserved).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223110r961131_rule","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:492","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223110","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59591","V-46727"],"severity":"medium"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"rule_id":"SV-223111r961131","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends configuring this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C38E2B-6C02-1014-A1A7-F15B832BC7C4","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:505","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223111","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59593","V-46729"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223111","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223111r961131_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Explorer).","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","group_id_src":"V-223111","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_version":"DTBI612-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C391AF-6C02-1014-AEE7-EFA1DB15198F","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_id":"SV-223112r961131","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223112","reference_identifier":"4095","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI614-IE11","third_party_tools":"","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:506","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223112","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59595","V-46731"],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"id":"V-223112","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (iexplore).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223112r961131_rule"},{"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3955F-6C02-1014-826E-B294E0E79EE1","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\ Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","rule_id":"SV-223113r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI630-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223113","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Reserved).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223113r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223113"},"legacy_ids":["SV-59597","V-46733"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:493","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223113","comments":null},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI635-IE11","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-223114","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Explorer).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223114r960963_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223114"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59645","V-46779"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:494","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223114","comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3A1D3-6C02-1014-9172-DA49E2A21828","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","rule_id":"SV-223114r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223115","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:495","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59647","V-46781"],"group_tree":{"id":"V-223115","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223115r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (iexplore).","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","group_id_src":"V-223115","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_version":"DTBI640-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223115r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C3A5EF-6C02-1014-954D-C905817C3EB5","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223116","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:496"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59653","V-46787"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223116","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223116r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Reserved).","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223116","rule_version":"DTBI645-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223116r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force the user to interact with a window containing malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and create windows that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C3A99F-6C02-1014-8DF2-8CA61B5291FF","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59655","V-46789"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223117","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:507","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Explorer).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223117r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223117","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223117","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI647-IE11","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","rule_id":"SV-223117r960963","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3AD2A-6C02-1014-9293-F37A05878646","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false"},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI649-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223118","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223118r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (iexplore).","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223118"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59657","V-46791"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:508"},"group_id":"V-223118","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C3B0BA-6C02-1014-876E-987D05B80197","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223118r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59663","V-46797"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:497","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223119","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223119r961863_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223119","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223119","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI650-IE11","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223119r961863","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.","uuid":"95C3B489-6C02-1014-B555-CB14B6BF3B7B","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59665","V-46799"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223120","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:498","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223120r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223120"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223120","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI655-IE11","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223120r961863","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\n","uuid":"95C3B83F-6C02-1014-8829-D80E2D7F8A85","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. It may be possible for malicious content hosted on a website to take advantage of these components. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components.","documentable":"false"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223121r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Scripting of Java applets)\n","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applets are exposed to scripts within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow scripts to access applets. If you disable this policy setting, scripts are prevented from accessing applets. If you do not configure this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. ","uuid":"95C3BE20-6C02-1014-B444-C31DF41EEC8E","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223121","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:499"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59667","V-46801"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223121","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223121r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Scripting of Java applets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223121","rule_version":"DTBI670-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223122r960963_rule","status":"open","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223122"},"legacy_ids":["SV-59673","V-46807"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223122","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml"},"group_id":"V-223122","comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI690-IE11","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223122","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\Use FormSuggest'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","rule_id":"SV-223122r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3C50E-6C02-1014-93A2-8A33B6F29A8C","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Use FormSuggest\" is REG_SZ = no, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This AutoComplete feature suggests possible matches when users are filling in forms. It is possible that this feature will cache sensitive data and store it in the user's profile, where it might not be protected as rigorously as required by organizational policy. If you enable this setting, the user is not presented with suggested matches when filling in forms. If you disable this setting, the user is presented with suggested possible matches when filling forms. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom to turn on the auto-complete feature for forms. To display this option, the user opens the Internet Options dialog box, clicks the \"Contents\" tab, and clicks the \"Settings\" button.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":""},{"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn Off Crash Detection)\n","rule_id":"SV-223123r960963","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"documentable":"false","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Restrictions Criteria: If the value \"NoCrashDetection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The 'Turn off Crash Detection' policy setting allows you to manage the crash detection feature of add-on management in Internet Explorer. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you enable this policy setting, a crash in Internet Explorer will be similar to one on a computer running Windows XP Professional Service Pack 1 and earlier, where Windows Error Reporting will be invoked. If you disable this policy setting, the crash detection feature in add-on management will be functional. ","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3C8DB-6C02-1014-9629-D7B2CFD3F9E5","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223123","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Crash Detection management must be enforced.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223123r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-223123","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:509"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59677","V-46811"],"severity":"medium","rule_version":"DTBI715-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223123"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59681","V-46815"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223124","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223124","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223124r960963_rule","status":"open","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223124"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223124","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI725-IE11","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223124r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' to 'Disabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found in user profile ntuser.dat file(s): 'Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FormSuggest PW Ask'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","uuid":"95C3CCCB-6C02-1014-899C-D202366BC90C","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' must be 'Disabled'. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest Passwords\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding. AND Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest PW Ask\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting controls automatic completion of fields in forms on web pages. It is possible that malware could be developed which would be able to extract the cached user names and passwords from the currently logged on user, which an attacker could then use to compromise that user's online accounts.  If you enable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for\" User names and passwords on forms\" will be turned on. If you disable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for \"User names and passwords on forms\" is turned off. The user also cannot opt to be prompted to save passwords. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom of turning on Auto Complete for \"User name and passwords on forms\", and the option of prompting to save passwords.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false"},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59685","V-46819"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223125","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:514","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223125r961083_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Managing SmartScreen Filter use must be enforced.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000206","id":"V-223125"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223125","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI740-IE11","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223125r961083","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"On\" from the drop-down box.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter)\n","uuid":"95C3D051-6C02-1014-A75A-8BF59A290626","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"On\" selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnabledV9\" is \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This setting is important from a security perspective because Microsoft has extensive data illustrating the positive impact the SmartScreen filter has had on reducing the risk of malware infection via visiting malicious websites. This policy setting allows users to enable the SmartScreen Filter, which will warn if the website being visited is known for fraudulent attempts to gather personal information through 'phishing' or is known to host malware. If you enable this setting the user will not be prompted to enable the SmartScreen Filter. It must be specified which mode the SmartScreen Filter uses: On or Off. If the feature is On, all website addresses not contained on the filters allow list, will be sent automatically to Microsoft without prompting the user. If this feature is set to Off, the feature will not run. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user is prompted to decide whether to turn on SmartScreen Filter during the first-run experience.","documentable":"false"},{"stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"ClearBrowsingHistoryOnExit\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Delete Browsing History on exit automatically deletes specified items when the last browser window closes.  Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures.  Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C3D427-6C02-1014-AA4E-EC3ABB88042C","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"rule_id":"SV-223126r960879","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' to 'Disabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Configure Delete Browsing History on exit)\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223126","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI760-IE11","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:516"},"group_id":"V-223126","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59695","V-46829"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000089","id":"V-223126"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223126r960879_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Browser must retain history on exit.","responsibility":""},{"rule_id_src":"SV-223127r960879_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Deleting websites that the user has visited must be disallowed.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223127","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59707","V-46841"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223127","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:517"},"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI770-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223127","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","rule_id":"SV-223127r960879","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited)\n","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C3D7CD-6C02-1014-BF9A-BFF2D4DA4AA5","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"CleanHistory\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy prevents users from deleting the history of websites the user has visited. If you enable this policy setting, websites the user has visited will be preserved when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you disable this policy setting, websites that the user has visited will be deleted when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you do not configure this policy setting, the user will be able to select whether to delete or preserve websites the user visited when the user clicks \"Delete\".","mitigations":""},{"rule_id":"SV-223128r960864","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\InPrivate\\Turn off InPrivate Browsing)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' to 'Enabled'.   ","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"InPrivate Browsing lets the user control whether or not Internet Explorer saves the browsing history, cookies, and other data. User control of settings is not the preferred control method. The InPrivate Browsing feature in Internet Explorer makes browser privacy easy by not storing history, cookies, temporary Internet files, or other data. If you enable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be disabled. If you disable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be available for use. If you do not configure this setting, InPrivate Browsing can be turned on or off through the registry.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"EnableInPrivateBrowsing\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","uuid":"95C3DB7D-6C02-1014-8D2C-B14D02CF4671","security_override_guidance":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223128","title":"SRG-APP-000080"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223128r960864_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"InPrivate Browsing must be disallowed.","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223128","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:518"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59713","V-46847"],"rule_version":"DTBI780-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","group_id_src":"V-223128","reference_identifier":"4095"},{"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223129r960963","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3DF30-6C02-1014-8448-92076085ECAA","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","documentable":"false","legacy_ids":["SV-59715","V-46849"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223129","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:519","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser control property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223129r960963_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223129"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223129","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI800-IE11"},{"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223130","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:520"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59719","V-46853"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223130"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223130r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Internet zone).","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223130","rule_version":"DTBI810-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223130r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\n","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","uuid":"95C3E2CE-6C02-1014-A6EA-B5EB0E86AB90","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223131r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","uuid":"95C3E6A0-6C02-1014-B0D1-83FC6A967455","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59723","V-46857"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223131","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:541","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223131r960963_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Reserved).","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223131","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223131","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI815-IE11","mitigation_control":""},{"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \" Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","uuid":"95C3EA3C-6C02-1014-A0A8-A3188C0D0ABB","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-223132r961863","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI820-IE11","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223132","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223132","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223132r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be set to prompt (Internet zone).","responsibility":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223132","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:521","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59725","V-46859"]},{"responsibility":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Explorer).","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223133r960963_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223133"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59727","V-46861"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:542","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223133","comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI825-IE11","group_id_src":"V-223133","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. ","rule_id":"SV-223133r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3ED9F-6C02-1014-BFAF-9697E2580FA4","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F"},{"group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223134","reference_identifier":"4095","rule_version":"DTBI830-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_id":"V-223134","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:522"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59729","V-46865"],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"id":"V-223134","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Internet zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223134r961092_rule","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; ' Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C3F1C0-6C02-1014-9167-C3BDD30C2106","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223134r961092"},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI835-IE11","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-223135","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223135r960963_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (iexplore).","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223135"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59735","V-46869"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-223135","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:543"},"documentable":"false","uuid":"95C3F5A7-6C02-1014-A088-B5411FA2D811","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-223135r960963","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","uuid":"95C3F93F-6C02-1014-B436-AC91F8E90207","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223136r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter must be Enabled and Enable selected)\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223136","rule_version":"DTBI840-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:523","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223136","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59745","V-46879"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223136"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223136r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter must be enforced (Internet zone).","responsibility":""},{"rule_id":"SV-223137r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\n","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C3FD1F-6C02-1014-8C2C-D7FB85A8A3F7","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser Control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser Control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","mitigations":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223137r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser Control must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223137","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59749","V-46883"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:524","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223137","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI850-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223137","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141"},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI860-IE11","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-223138","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Restricted Sites zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223138r960963_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223138"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":["SV-59751","V-46885"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223138","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:525","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C40181-6C02-1014-88B8-8537B8EE1D5B","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223138r960963","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59755","V-46889"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:526"},"group_id":"V-223139","comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223139r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223139"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223139","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI870-IE11","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\n","rule_id":"SV-223139r961863","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C4052B-6C02-1014-8D7A-8877B66C792C","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \"Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false"},{"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C40C0C-6C02-1014-B8F5-F760CABF4C9E","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\n","rule_id":"SV-223140r961092","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI880-IE11","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223140","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","weight":"10.0","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223140r961092_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000210","id":"V-223140"},"legacy_ids":["SV-59759","V-46893"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:527"},"group_id":"V-223140","comments":null},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter)\n","rule_id":"SV-223141r960963","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C411B9-6C02-1014-8E75-AA8CDEDABE73","documentable":"false","group_id":"V-223141","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:528","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59761","V-46895"],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223141","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter property must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223141r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223141","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI890-IE11","third_party_tools":""},{"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI900-IE11","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-223142","reference_identifier":"4095","group_tree":{"id":"V-223142","title":"SRG-APP-000112"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Reserved).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223142r960921_rule","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:529"},"group_id":"V-223142","comments":null,"legacy_ids":["SV-59763","V-46897"],"severity":"medium","documentable":"false","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C41573-6C02-1014-B691-9C0AE1AB9E45","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict ActiveX Install\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   ","rule_id":"SV-223142r960921","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001695"]},{"stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause them to perform an undesirable action. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","uuid":"95C41908-6C02-1014-B317-895AA6C6D799","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223143r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disable selected)\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223143","rule_version":"DTBI910-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223143","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:530"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59769","V-46903"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223143"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223143r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","responsibility":""},{"ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-223144r961863","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\n","uuid":"95C41CA8-6C02-1014-92E0-D3D62B84D890","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"Unsigned components are more likely to contain malicious code and it is more difficult to determine the author of the application - therefore they should be avoided if possible. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59773","V-46907"],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:531","href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-223144","rule_id_src":"SV-223144r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223144","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223144","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI920-IE11","mitigation_control":""},{"stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"It may be possible for someone to host malicious content on a website that takes advantage of these components. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components.","uuid":"95C42067-6C02-1014-97A4-9EB6ED39D333","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"rule_id":"SV-223145r961863","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223145","rule_version":"DTBI930-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223145","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:532"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59787","V-46921"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000516","id":"V-223145"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223145r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":""},{"weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223146","rule_version":"DTBI940-IE11","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-223146","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:533"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59793","V-46927"],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000141","id":"V-223146"},"rule_id_src":"SV-223146r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","mitigations":"","uuid":"95C423EE-6C02-1014-B06F-DAF24111B53E","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-223146r960963","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\n"},{"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223147","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI950-IE11","legacy_ids":["SV-59805","V-46939"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:534"},"group_id":"V-223147","comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223147r960963_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223147","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C4274D-6C02-1014-B67D-84ABC9D1E2AB","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause an undesirable action. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disabled selected)\n","rule_id":"SV-223147r960963"},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI985-IE11","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-223148","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","weight":"10.0","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"When Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled, ActiveX controls must be disallowed to run in Protected Mode.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-223148r961863_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-223148","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"legacy_ids":["SV-59841","V-46975"],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:556"},"group_id":"V-223148","comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C42ADC-6C02-1014-A1F6-99DEEA633AB4","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"DisableEPMCompat\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","discussion":"This setting prevents ActiveX controls from running in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled. When a user has an ActiveX control installed that is not compatible with Enhanced Protected Mode and a website attempts to load the control, Internet Explorer notifies the user and gives the option to run the website in regular Protected Mode. This policy setting disables this notification and forces all websites to run in Enhanced Protected Mode. Enhanced Protected Mode provides additional protection against malicious websites by using 64-bit processes on 64-bit versions of Windows. For computers running at least Windows 8, Enhanced Protected Mode also limits the locations Internet Explorer can read from in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not give the user the option to disable Enhanced Protected Mode. All Protected Mode websites will run in Enhanced Protected Mode. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer notifies users and provides an option to run websites with incompatible ActiveX controls in regular Protected Mode.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' to 'Enabled'.   ","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Advanced Page/Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode )\n","rule_id":"SV-223148r961863","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59847","V-46981"],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-223149","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:547"},"comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Internet zone).","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-223149r1117169_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000039","id":"V-223149"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-223149","reference_identifier":"4095","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI990-IE11","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows)\n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   ","rule_id":"SV-223149r1117169","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"95C42E39-6C02-1014-99D2-CD360D32D80A","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","documentable":"false"},{"uuid":"95C431D0-6C02-1014-A9D8-8ABCB286C1F9","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DOD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by allowing the user to turn on/off support for TLS and SSL. TLS is a protocol for protecting communications between the browser and the target server. When the browser attempts to set up a protected communication with the target server, the browser and server negotiate which protocol and version to use. The browser and server attempt to match each other's list of supported protocols and versions and pick the most preferred match.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","mitigations":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" must be \"Enabled\".\n\nVerify the only option selected is \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings!SecureProtocols.\n\nCriteria: If the value for \"SecureProtocols\" is not REG_DWORD = \"2048\", this is a finding.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-250540r1117186","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('turn off encryption support' setting is handled by Group Policy.)\nTest            :   false (TLS 1.2 must be selected for the IE option 'turn off encryption support' via Group Policy.)\nResult Analysis :        HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\SecureProtocols\\value = '2560' failed test of 'equals' compared to '2048' \n","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSelect only \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.","group_id_src":"V-250540","reference_identifier":"4095","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI014-IE11","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-59337","V-46473"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-250540","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:580"},"status":"open","rule_id_src":"SV-250540r1117186_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Turn off Encryption Support must be enabled.","group_tree":{"id":"V-250540","title":"SRG-APP-000416"},"false_positives":""},{"rule_id":"SV-250541r1117186","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"No Sites\" from the drop-down box.\n","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Allow insecure fallback for:' set to 'No Sites')\n","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"95C4356C-6C02-1014-9FA4-950F0AB3F6CA","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"No Sites\" selected from the drop-down box. If \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" is not \"Enabled\" or any other drop-down option is selected, this is a finding. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableSSL3Fallback\" is REG_DWORD=0, this is not a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DoD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by blocking an insecure fallback to SSL when TLS 1.0 or greater fails.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","rule_id_src":"SV-250541r1117186_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer) must be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-250541","title":"SRG-APP-000416"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":["SV-79219","V-64729"],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-250541","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:581"},"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"DTBI1100-IE11","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-250541","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416"},{"ccis":["CCI-002605"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-252910r1156566","fix_text":"Remove the Internet Explorer 11 application.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:19:26\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Internet Explorer 11 is installed)\n","uuid":"95C43924-6C02-1014-A698-98014C5CC808","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"95B6BE82-6C02-1014-94FF-91E32281DA5F","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Internet Explorer 11 is no longer supported by the vendor.\n\nIf Internet Explorer 11 is installed, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously.\n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw).\n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality, will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may depend on the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.","documentable":"false","severity":"high","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.win:def:252910"},"group_id":"V-252910","rule_id_src":"SV-252910r1156566_rule","status":"open","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The version of Internet Explorer running on the system must be a supported version.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-APP-000456","id":"V-252910"},"reference_identifier":"4095","group_id_src":"V-252910","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"DTBI999-IE11"}],"reference_identifier":"4095"},{"version":"2","size":263,"stig_id":"Microsoft_Windows_11_STIG","release_info":"Release: 6 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","display_name":"Microsoft Windows 11","stig_name":"Microsoft Windows 11 Security Technical Implementation Guide","uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","rules":[{"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253254","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253254","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253254"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Domain-joined systems must use Windows 11 Enterprise Edition 64-bit version.","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_applicable","rule_id_src":"SV-253254r991589_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-253254","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_version":"WN11-00-000005","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","fix_text":"Use Windows 11 Enterprise 64-bit version for domain-joined systems.","rule_id":"SV-253254r991589","mitigations":"","discussion":"Features such as Credential Guard use virtualization-based security to protect information that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. There are a number of system requirements that must be met in order for Credential Guard to be configured and enabled properly. Virtualization-based security and Credential Guard are only available with Windows 11 Enterprise 64-bit version.","check_content":"Verify domain-joined systems are using Windows 11 Enterprise Edition 64-bit version.\n\nFor standalone systems, this is NA.\n\nOpen \"Settings\".\n\nSelect \"System\", then \"About\".\n\nIf \"Edition\" is not \"Windows 11 Enterprise\", this is a finding.\n\nIf \"System type\" is not \"64-bit operating system...\", this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1333616-6C02-1014-B2D8-F703352F0DCA","documentable":"false"},{"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253255"},"group_id":"V-253255","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"id":"V-253255","title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 domain-joined systems must have a Trusted Platform Module (TPM) enabled.","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_applicable","rule_id_src":"SV-253255r1117271_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-253255","reference_identifier":"5471","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000010","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-002421"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","fix_text":"For standalone systems, this is NA.\n\nVirtualization-based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nEnsure domain-joined systems must have a TPM that is configured for use. (Versions 2.0 support Credential Guard.)\n\nThe TPM must be enabled in the firmware.\nRun \"tpm.msc\" for configuration options in Windows.","rule_id":"SV-253255r1117271","discussion":"Credential Guard uses virtualization-based security to protect information that could be used in credential theft attacks if compromised. There are a number of system requirements that must be met in order for Credential Guard to be configured and enabled properly. Without a TPM enabled and ready for use, Credential Guard keys are stored in a less secure method using software.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify domain-joined systems have a TPM enabled and ready for use.\n\nFor standalone systems, this is NA.\n\nVirtualization-based security, including Credential Guard, currently cannot be implemented in virtual desktop implementations (VDI) due to specific supporting requirements including a TPM, UEFI with Secure Boot, and the capability to run the Hyper-V feature within the virtual desktop.\n\nFor VDIs where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nVerify the system has a TPM and is ready for use.\nRun \"tpm.msc\".\nReview the sections in the center pane.\n\"Status\" must indicate it has been configured with a message such as \"The TPM is ready for use\" or \"The TPM is on and ownership has been taken\".\nTPM Manufacturer Information - Specific Version = 2.0\n\nIf a TPM is not found or is not ready for use, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F13342BF-6C02-1014-8532-8DB6657A2E29","documentable":"false"},{"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253256","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253256"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253256","title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253256r1117271_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must have Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI) firmware and be configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253256","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000015","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-002421"],"rule_id":"SV-253256r1117271","fix_text":"Configure UEFI firmware to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS mode.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Unified Extensible Firmware Interface (UEFI) firmware must exist and be configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.)\n","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"For virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nVerify the system firmware is configured to run in UEFI mode, not Legacy BIOS.\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", if \"BIOS Mode\" does not display \"UEFI\", this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"UEFI provides additional security features in comparison to legacy BIOS firmware, including Secure Boot. UEFI is required to support additional security features in Windows 11, including virtualization-based Security and Credential Guard. Systems with UEFI that are operating in Legacy BIOS mode will not support these security features.","uuid":"F1334808-6C02-1014-A9B2-EED730E74347","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-002421"],"rule_id":"SV-253257r1117271","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Run a PowerShell command to determine if Secure Boot must be enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        'False' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'True' \n","fix_text":"Enable Secure Boot in the system firmware.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"Secure Boot is a standard that ensures systems boot only to a trusted operating system. Secure Boot is required to support additional security features in Windows 11, including virtualization-based Security and Credential Guard. If Secure Boot is turned off, these security features will not function.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the system firmware is configured for Secure Boot.\n\nFor virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nRun \"System Information\".\n\nUnder \"System Summary\", if \"Secure Boot State\" does not display \"On\", this is a finding.","uuid":"F1334CAB-6C02-1014-85FC-8C83B16FC343","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253257"},"group_id":"V-253257","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"group_tree":{"id":"V-253257","title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188"},"false_positives":"","status":"open","rule_id_src":"SV-253257r1117271_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Secure Boot must be enabled on Windows 11 systems.","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000424-GPOS-00188","group_id_src":"V-253257","reference_identifier":"5471","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000020","third_party_tools":""},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000025","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-253258","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080","status":"not_reviewed","rule_id_src":"SV-253258r1000099_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 must employ automated mechanisms to determine the state of system components with regard to flaw remediation using the following frequency: Continuously, where ESS is used; 30 days, for any additional internal network scans not covered by ESS; and annually, for external scans by Computer Network Defense Service Provider (CNDSP).","group_tree":{"id":"V-253258","title":"SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:901"},"group_id":"V-253258","documentable":"false","uuid":"F133511D-6C02-1014-BE6D-FED0F41AC049","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"An approved tool for continuous network scanning must be installed and configured to run.\n\nWithout the use of automated mechanisms to scan for security flaws on a continuous and/or periodic basis, the operating system or other system components may remain vulnerable to the exploits presented by undetected software flaws.\n\nTo support this requirement, the operating system may have an integrated solution incorporating continuous scanning using ESS and periodic scanning using other tools, as specified in the requirement.","check_content":"Verify DOD-approved ESS software is installed and properly operating. Ask the site information system security manager (ISSM) for documentation of the ESS software installation and configuration.\n\nIf the ISSM is not able to provide a documented configuration for an installed ESS or if the ESS software is not properly maintained or used, this is a finding.\n\nNote: Example of documentation can be a copy of the site's CCB approved Software Baseline with version of software noted or a memo from the ISSM stating current ESS software and version.","rule_id":"SV-253258r1000099","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253258, SV-253258r1000099, SRG-OS-000191-GPOS-00080)\n","fix_text":"Install DOD-approved ESS software and ensure it is operating continuously.","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1335582-6C02-1014-AD1D-A3DE71AC2855","check_content":"Verify all Windows 11 information systems (including SIPRNet) employ BitLocker for full disk encryption.\n\nFor virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) in which the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\nFor AVD implementations with no data at rest, this is NA.\n\nIf full disk encryption using BitLocker is not implemented, this is a finding.\n\nVerify BitLocker is turned on for the operating system drive and any fixed data drives.\n\nOpen \"BitLocker Drive Encryption\" from the Control Panel.\n\nIf the operating system drive or any fixed data drives have \"Turn on BitLocker\", this is a finding.\n\nNote: An alternate encryption application may be used in lieu of BitLocker providing it is configured for full disk encryption and satisfies the pre-boot authentication requirements (WN11-00-000031 and WN11-00-000032).","discussion":"If data at rest is unencrypted, it is vulnerable to disclosure. Even if the operating system enforces permissions on data access, an adversary can remove non-volatile memory and read it directly, thereby circumventing operating system controls. Encrypting the data ensures that confidentiality is protected even when the operating system is not running.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-002475"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Enable full disk encryption on all information systems (including SIPRNet) using BitLocker.\n\nBitLocker, included in Windows, can be enabled in the Control Panel under \"BitLocker Drive Encryption\" as well as other management tools.\n\nNote: An alternate encryption application may be used in lieu of BitLocker providing it is configured for full disk encryption and satisfies the pre-boot authentication requirements (WN11-00-000031 and WN11-00-000032).","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (BitLocker must be enabled on all fixed drives.)\nResult Analysis :          protectionstatus = '0' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \n","rule_id":"SV-253259r958870","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253259","group_title":"SRG-OS-000404-GPOS-00183","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000030","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"high","group_id":"V-253259","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253259"},"comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 information systems must use BitLocker to encrypt all disks to protect the confidentiality and integrity of all information at rest.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253259r958870_rule","status":"open","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000404-GPOS-00183","id":"V-253259"}},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-002476"],"rule_id":"SV-253260r958872","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; BitLocker Drive Encryption &gt;&gt; Operating System Drives \"Require additional authentication at startup\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Configure TPM Startup PIN:\" set to \"Require startup PIN with TPM\" or with \"Configure TPM startup key and PIN:\" set to \"Require startup key and PIN with TPM\".","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :         false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :           false ('Configure TPM startup PIN' is set to 'Require startup PIN with TPM'.)\nResult Analysis :                HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\UseTPMPIN\\value = '2' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \nTest            :           false ('Configure TPM startup key and PIN' is set to 'Require startup key and PIN with TPM'.)\nResult Analysis :                HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\UseTPMKeyPIN\\value = '2' failed test of 'equals' compared to '1' \nTest            :         true ('Allow network unlock at startup' is Enabled.) (negated)\nCriteria        :       false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :         true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :           true ('Configure TPM startup PIN' is set to 'Allow startup PIN with TPM'.)\nTest            :           true ('Configure TPM startup key and PIN' is set to 'Allow startup key and PIN with TPM'.)\nTest            :         false ('Allow network unlock at startup' is Enabled.)\nResult Analysis :              Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\OSManageNKP'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :     true ('Require additional authentication at startup' is Enabled.)\n","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nFor virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) in which the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nFor AVD implementations with no data at rest, this is NA.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\\n\nValue Name: UseAdvancedStartup\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf one of the following registry values does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\\n\nValue Name: UseTPMPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nValue Name: UseTPMKeyPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nWhen BitLocker network unlock is used:\n\nValue Name: UseTPMPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)\n\nValue Name: UseTPMKeyPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000002 (2)\n\nBitLocker network unlock may be used in conjunction with a BitLocker PIN. See the article below regarding information about network unlock.\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/information-protection/bitlocker/bitlocker-how-to-enable-network-unlock","discussion":"If data at rest is unencrypted, it is vulnerable to disclosure. Even if the operating system enforces permissions on data access, an adversary can remove non-volatile memory and read it directly, thereby circumventing operating system controls. Encrypting the data ensures that confidentiality is protected even when the operating system is not running. Pre-boot authentication prevents unauthorized users from accessing encrypted drives.","mitigations":"","uuid":"F13359E3-6C02-1014-9935-DE519DE135EE","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","comments":null,"group_id":"V-253260","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253260"},"severity":"high","legacy_ids":[],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253260","title":"SRG-OS-000405-GPOS-00184"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253260r958872_rule","status":"open","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must use a BitLocker PIN for pre-boot authentication.","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000405-GPOS-00184","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253260","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000031","third_party_tools":""},{"group_tree":{"id":"V-253261","title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253261r958504_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must use a BitLocker PIN with a minimum length of six digits for pre-boot authentication.","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253261"},"group_id":"V-253261","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000032","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000121-GPOS-00062","group_id_src":"V-253261","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_id":"SV-253261r958504","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (BitLocker must be 6 digits or more.)\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; BitLocker Drive Encryption &gt;&gt; Operating System Drives \"Configure minimum PIN length for startup\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Minimum characters:\" set to \"6\" or greater.","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000804"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"If data at rest is unencrypted, it is vulnerable to disclosure. Even if the operating system enforces permissions on data access, an adversary can remove non-volatile memory and read it directly, thereby circumventing operating system controls. Encrypting the data ensures that confidentiality is protected even when the operating system is not running. Pre-boot authentication prevents unauthorized users from accessing encrypted drives. Increasing the pin length requires a greater number of guesses for an attacker.","check_content":"If the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nFor virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) in which the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, this is NA.\n\nFor AVD implementations with no data at rest, this is NA.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\FVE\\\n\nValue Name: MinimumPIN\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000006 (6) or greater","uuid":"F1335E61-6C02-1014-ABE2-A16350934827","security_override_guidance":""},{"documentable":"false","uuid":"F13362D8-6C02-1014-B0AE-D58F4D391256","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the operating system employs a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs. This must include packaged apps such as the universal apps installed by default on systems.\n\nIf an application allowlisting program is not in use on the system, this is a finding.\n\nConfiguration of allowlisting applications will vary by the program.\n\nAppLocker is an allowlisting application built into Windows 11 Enterprise. A deny-by-default implementation is initiated by enabling any AppLocker rules within a category, only allowing what is specified by defined rules.\n\nIf AppLocker is used, perform the following to view the configuration of AppLocker:\nRun \"PowerShell\".\n\nExecute the following command, substituting [c:\\temp\\file.xml] with a location and file name appropriate for the system:\nGet-AppLockerPolicy -Effective -XML &gt; c:\\temp\\file.xml\n\nThis will produce an xml file with the effective settings that can be viewed in a browser or opened in a program such as Excel for review.\n\nImplementation guidance for AppLocker is available at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/threat-protection/windows-defender-application-control/applocker/applocker-policies-deployment-guide","mitigations":"","discussion":"Utilizing an allowlist provides a configuration management method for allowing the execution of only authorized software. Using only authorized software decreases risk by limiting the number of potential vulnerabilities.\n\nThe organization must identify authorized software programs and only permit execution of authorized software. The process used to identify software programs that are authorized to execute on organizational information systems is commonly referred to as allowlisting.","rule_id":"SV-253262r958808","fix_text":"Configure an application allowlisting program to employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.\n\nConfiguration of allowlisting applications will vary by the program. AppLocker is an allowlisting application built into Windows 11 Enterprise.\n\nIf AppLocker is used, it is configured through group policy in Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Application Control Policies &gt;&gt; AppLocker.\n\nImplementation guidance for AppLocker is available in the NSA paper \"Application allowlisting using Microsoft AppLocker\" at the following link:\n\nhttps://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/security/threat-protection/windows-defender-application-control/applocker/applocker-policies-deployment-guide","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253262, SV-253262r958808, SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155)\n","ccis":["CCI-001774"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000035","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253262","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","rule_id_src":"SV-253262r958808_rule","status":"not_reviewed","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The operating system must employ a deny-all, permit-by-exception policy to allow the execution of authorized software programs.","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000370-GPOS-00155","id":"V-253262"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253262","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:1701","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml"}},{"fix_text":"Update systems on the Semi-Annual Channel to \"Microsoft Windows 11 Version 22H2 (OS Build 22621.380)\" or greater.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 22621)\n","rule_id":"SV-253263r1016364","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"documentable":"false","check_content":"Run \"winver.exe\".\n\nIf the \"About Windows\" dialog box does not display \"Microsoft Windows 11 Version 22H2 (OS Build 22621.380)\" or greater, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Windows 11 is maintained by Microsoft at servicing levels for specific periods of time to support Windows as a Service. Systems at unsupported servicing levels or releases will not receive security updates for new vulnerabilities which leaves them subject to exploitation.\n\nNew versions with feature updates are planned to be released on a semi-annual basis with an estimated support timeframe of 18 to 30 months depending on the release. Support for previously released versions has been extended for Enterprise editions.\n\nA separate servicing branch intended for special purpose systems is the Long-Term Servicing Channel (LTSC, formerly Branch - LTSB) which will receive security updates for 10 years but excludes feature updates.","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133671F-6C02-1014-A6C4-FF80C1F925B2","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253263"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must be maintained at a supported servicing level.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253263r1016364_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253263","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253263","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"high","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000040","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253263"},{"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1336B44-6C02-1014-8643-EB7C4D2947F1","check_content":"Verify an antivirus solution is installed on the system and in use. The antivirus solution may be bundled with an approved Endpoint Security Solution.\n\nVerify if Microsoft Defender Antivirus is in use or enabled:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*Defender*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\"\n\nVerify third-party antivirus is in use or enabled:\n\nOpen \"PowerShell\".\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*mcafee*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\"\n\nEnter \"get-service | where {$_.DisplayName -Like \"*symantec*\"} | Select Status,DisplayName\"\n\nIf there is no antivirus solution installed on the system, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Malicious software can establish a base on individual desktops and servers. Employing an automated mechanism to detect this type of software will aid in elimination of the software from the operating system.","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Install Microsoft Defender Antivirus or a third-party antivirus solution.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Windows must use an antivirus program)\n","rule_id":"SV-253264r991589","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000045","mitigation_control":"","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253264","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","weight":"10.0","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Windows 11 system must use an antivirus program.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253264r991589_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253264"},"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"high","group_id":"V-253264","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253264"},"comments":null},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000213"],"fix_text":"Format all local volumes to use NTFS.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Local volumes use NTFS)\n","rule_id":"SV-253265r1137691","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to Storage &gt;&gt; Disk Management.\n\nIf the \"File System\" column does not indicate \"NTFS\" for each volume assigned a drive letter, this is a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to system partitions such the Recovery and EFI System Partition.","discussion":"The ability to set access permissions and auditing is critical to maintaining the security and proper access controls of a system. To support this, volumes must be formatted using the NTFS file system.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1336F6F-6C02-1014-B4F1-E0F3245D972D","documentable":"false","group_id":"V-253265","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253265"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"high","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253265","title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Local volumes must be formatted using NTFS.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253265r1137691_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000080-GPOS-00048","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253265","rule_version":"WN11-00-000050","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253266","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253266"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253266","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253266r991589_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Alternate operating systems must not be permitted on the same system.","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253266","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000055","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"rule_id":"SV-253266r991589","fix_text":"Ensure Windows 11 is the only operating system on a device. Remove alternate operating systems.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Review Installed OS via PowerShell)\n","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the system does not include other operating system installations.\n\nRun \"Advanced System Settings\".\nSelect the \"Advanced\" tab.\nClick the \"Settings\" button in the \"Startup and Recovery\" section.\n\nIf the drop-down list box \"Default operating system:\" shows any operating system other than Windows 11, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Allowing other operating systems to run on a secure system may allow security to be circumvented.","uuid":"F1337384-6C02-1014-8A16-B41A6CAC204C","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133779F-6C02-1014-8D06-98FB151A38C1","discussion":"Shares which provide network access, must not exist on a workstation except for system-created administrative shares, and could potentially expose sensitive information. If a share is necessary, share permissions, as well as NTFS permissions, must be reconfigured to give the minimum access to those accounts that require it.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Non-system-created shares must not exist on workstations.\n\nIf only system-created shares exist on the system, this is NA.\n\nRun \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Shared Folders &gt;&gt; Shares.\n\nIf the only shares listed are \"ADMIN$\", \"C$\" and \"IPC$\", this is NA.\n(Selecting Properties for system-created shares will display a message that it has been shared for administrative purposes.)\n\nRight-click any non-system-created shares.\nSelect \"Properties\".\nSelect the \"Share Permissions\" tab.\n\nVerify the necessity of any shares found.\nIf the file shares have not been reconfigured to restrict permissions to the specific groups or accounts that require access, this is a finding.\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nIf the NTFS permissions have not been reconfigured to restrict permissions to the specific groups or accounts that require access, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-001090"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253267, SV-253267r1137695, SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069)\n","fix_text":"If a non-system-created share is required on a system, configure the share and NTFS permissions to limit access to the specific groups or accounts that require it.\n\nRemove any unnecessary non-system-created shares.","rule_id":"SV-253267r1137695","group_id_src":"V-253267","reference_identifier":"5471","group_title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000060","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-253267","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:2701","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml"},"comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Non-system-created file shares on a system must limit access to groups that require it.","status":"not_reviewed","rule_id_src":"SV-253267r1137695_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000138-GPOS-00069","id":"V-253267"},"false_positives":""},{"ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-003627","CCI-000795"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253268r1051039","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-253268, SV-253268r1051039, SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212)\n","fix_text":"Review local accounts and verify their necessity. Disable or delete any active accounts that have not been used in the last 35 days.","uuid":"F1337BB9-6C02-1014-8B4C-8652508BA861","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"Outdated or unused accounts provide penetration points that may go undetected. Inactive accounts must be deleted if no longer necessary or, if still required, disable until needed.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212, SRG-OS-000118-GPOS-00060","check_content":"Run \"PowerShell\".\nCopy the lines below to the PowerShell window and enter.\n\n\"([ADSI]('WinNT://{0}' -f $env:COMPUTERNAME)).Children | Where { $_.SchemaClassName -eq 'user' } | ForEach {\n  $user = ([ADSI]$_.Path)\n  $lastLogin = $user.Properties.LastLogin.Value\n  $enabled = ($user.Properties.UserFlags.Value -band 0x2) -ne 0x2\n  if ($lastLogin -eq $null) {\n   $lastLogin = 'Never'\n  }\n  Write-Host $user.Name $lastLogin $enabled \n}\"\n\nThis will return a list of local accounts with the account name, last logon, and if the account is enabled (True/False).\nFor example: User1 10/31/2015 5:49:56 AM True\n\nReview the list to determine the finding validity for each account reported.\n\nExclude the following accounts:\nBuilt-in administrator account (Disabled, SID ending in 500)\nBuilt-in guest account (Disabled, SID ending in 501)\nBuilt-in DefaultAccount (Disabled, SID ending in 503)\nLocal administrator account\n\nIf any enabled accounts have not been logged on to within the past 35 days, this is a finding.\n\nInactive accounts that have been reviewed and deemed to be required must be documented with the information system security officer (ISSO).","documentable":"false","severity":"low","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253268","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:2901"},"status":"not_reviewed","rule_id_src":"SV-253268r1051039_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Unused accounts must be disabled or removed from the system after 35 days of inactivity.","group_tree":{"id":"V-253268","title":"SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-253268","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000468-GPOS-00212","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000065","mitigation_control":""},{"ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"An account that does not have Administrator duties must not have Administrator rights. Such rights would allow the account to bypass or modify required security restrictions on that machine and make it vulnerable to attack.\n\nSystem administrators must log on to systems only using accounts with the minimum level of authority necessary.\n\nFor domain-joined workstations, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain workstation administrator group (see V-36434 in the Active Directory Domain STIG). Restricting highly privileged accounts from the local Administrators group helps mitigate the risk of privilege escalation resulting from credential theft attacks.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local administrators group.","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Groups.\nReview the members of the Administrators group.\nOnly the appropriate administrator groups or accounts responsible for administration of the system may be members of the group.\n\nFor domain-joined workstations, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain workstation administrator group.\n\nStandard user accounts must not be members of the local administrator group.\n\nIf prohibited accounts are members of the local administrators group, this is a finding.\n\nThe built-in Administrator account or other required administrative accounts would not be a finding.","uuid":"F13381EE-6C02-1014-90A7-BEC34D9EC407","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-002165"],"rule_id":"SV-253269r958702","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-253269, SV-253269r958702, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123)\n","fix_text":"Configure the system to include only administrator groups or accounts that are responsible for the system in the local Administrators group.\n\nFor domain-joined workstations, the Domain Admins group must be replaced by a domain workstation administrator group.\n\nRemove any standard user accounts.","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123","group_id_src":"V-253269","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_version":"WN11-00-000070","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:3101"},"group_id":"V-253269","severity":"high","legacy_ids":[],"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00123","id":"V-253269"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_reviewed","rule_id_src":"SV-253269r958702_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Only accounts responsible for the administration of a system must have Administrator rights on the system."},{"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F13387B8-6C02-1014-BFC3-CE6DF1EADC92","mitigations":"","discussion":"Backup Operators are able to read and write to any file in the system, regardless of the rights assigned to it. Backup and restore rights permit users to circumvent the file access restrictions present on NTFS disk drives for backup and restore purposes. Members of the Backup Operators group must have separate logon accounts for performing backup duties.","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Groups.\nReview the members of the Backup Operators group.\n\nIf the group contains no accounts, this is not a finding.\n\nIf the group contains any accounts, the accounts must be specifically for backup functions.\n\nIf the group contains any standard user accounts used for performing normal user tasks, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253270, SV-253270r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","fix_text":"Create separate accounts for backup operations for users with this privilege.","rule_id":"SV-253270r991589","group_id_src":"V-253270","reference_identifier":"5471","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000075","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:3301"},"group_id":"V-253270","comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Only accounts responsible for the backup operations must be members of the Backup Operators group.","status":"not_reviewed","rule_id_src":"SV-253270r991589_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253270"},"false_positives":""},{"reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253271","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000080","mitigation_control":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:3501","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml"},"group_id":"V-253271","rule_id_src":"SV-253271r958702_rule","status":"not_reviewed","rule_title":"Only authorized user accounts must be allowed to create or run virtual machines on Windows 11 systems.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124","id":"V-253271"},"uuid":"F1338C4F-6C02-1014-B5DC-958C1E455C16","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"If a hosted hypervisor (Hyper-V, VMware Workstation, etc.) is installed on the system, verify only authorized user accounts are allowed to run virtual machines.\n\nFor Hyper-V, run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Groups.\nDouble click on \"Hyper-V Administrators\".\n\nIf any unauthorized groups or user accounts are listed in \"Members:\", this is a finding.\n\nFor hosted hypervisors other than Hyper-V, verify only authorized user accounts have access to run the virtual machines. Restrictions may be enforced by access to the physical system, software restriction policies, or access restrictions built into the application.\n\nIf any unauthorized groups or user accounts have access to create or run virtual machines, this is a finding.\n\nAll users authorized to create or run virtual machines must be documented with the ISSM/ISSO. Accounts nested within group accounts must be documented as individual accounts and not the group accounts.","discussion":"Allowing other operating systems to run on a secure system may allow users to circumvent security. For Hyper-V, preventing unauthorized users from being assigned to the Hyper-V Administrators group will prevent them from accessing or creating virtual machines on the system. The Hyper-V Hypervisor is used by virtualization-based Security features such as Credential Guard on Windows 11; however, it is not the full Hyper-V installation.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-002165"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253271r958702","fix_text":"For Hyper-V, remove any unauthorized groups or user accounts from the \"Hyper-V Administrators\" group.\n\nFor hosted hypervisors other than Hyper-V, restrict access to create or run virtual machines to authorized user accounts only.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253271, SV-253271r958702, SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00124)\n"},{"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT III, V-253272, SV-253272r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","fix_text":"Limit local user accounts on domain-joined systems. Remove any unauthorized local accounts.","rule_id":"SV-253272r991589","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1339054-6C02-1014-8677-B3D7FE669599","mitigations":"","discussion":"To minimize potential points of attack, local user accounts, other than built-in accounts and local administrator accounts, must not exist on a workstation in a domain. Users must log on to workstations in a domain with their domain accounts.","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Users.\n\nIf local users other than the accounts listed below exist on a workstation in a domain, this is a finding. \n\nFor standalone or nondomain-joined systems, this is Not Applicable.\n\nBuilt-in Administrator account (Disabled)\nBuilt-in Guest account (Disabled)\nBuilt-in DefaultAccount (Disabled)\nBuilt-in defaultuser0 (Disabled)\nBuilt-in WDAGUtilityAccount (Disabled)\nLocal administrator account(s)\n\nAll of the built-in accounts may not exist on a system, depending on the Windows 11 version.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Standard local user accounts must not exist on a system in a domain.","status":"not_reviewed","rule_id_src":"SV-253272r991589_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-253272","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"low","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:3701","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml"},"group_id":"V-253272","comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000085","group_id_src":"V-253272","reference_identifier":"5471","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","weight":"10.0"},{"group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-253273","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_version":"WN11-00-000090","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_id":"V-253273","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253273","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","id":"V-253273"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Accounts must be configured to require password expiration.","potential_impacts":"","status":"open","rule_id_src":"SV-253273r1051040_rule","discussion":"Passwords that do not expire increase exposure with a greater probability of being discovered or cracked.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Run \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Users.\nDouble-click each active account.\n\nIf \"Password never expires\" is selected for any account, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133947D-6C02-1014-8460-F422C0A20A4F","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000199"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Accounts must be configured to require password expiration.)\nResult Analysis :        Existence requirement is 'none_exists' and 1 collected item exists, so result is false\n","fix_text":"Configure all passwords to expire.\nRun \"Computer Management\".\nNavigate to System Tools &gt;&gt; Local Users and Groups &gt;&gt; Users.\nDouble-click each active account.\nEnsure \"Password never expires\" is not checked on all active accounts.","rule_id":"SV-253273r1051040"},{"group_id_src":"V-253274","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000095","mitigation_control":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253274","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml"},"group_id":"V-253274","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253274r1016661_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Permissions for system files and directories must conform to minimum requirements.","group_tree":{"id":"V-253274","title":"SRG-OS-000312-GPOS-00122"},"false_positives":"","uuid":"F13398E0-6C02-1014-A227-9F2BBDAC1CBD","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"Changing the system's file and directory permissions allows the possibility of unauthorized and anonymous modification to the operating system and installed applications.","mitigations":"","check_content":"The default file system permissions are adequate when the Security Option \"Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" is set to \"Disabled\" (WN11-SO-000160).\n\nIf the default file system permissions are maintained and the referenced option is set to \"Disabled\", this is not a finding.\n\nVerify the default permissions for the sample directories below. Non-privileged groups such as Users or Authenticated Users must not have greater than read &amp; execute permissions except where noted as defaults. (Individual accounts must not be used to assign permissions.)\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab, and the \"Advanced\" button.\n\nC:\\\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nAdministrators - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files\nSYSTEM - Full control - This folder, subfolders, and files\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nAuthenticated Users - Modify - Subfolders and files only\nAuthenticated Users - Create folders / append data - This folder only\n\n\\Program Files\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\n\n\\Windows\nType - \"Allow\" for all\nInherited from - \"None\" for all\nPrincipal - Access - Applies to\nTrustedInstaller - Full control - This folder and subfolders\nSYSTEM - Modify - This folder only\nSYSTEM - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nAdministrators - Modify - This folder only\nAdministrators - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nUsers - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nCREATOR OWNER - Full control - Subfolders and files only\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES - Read &amp; execute - This folder, subfolders, and files\n\nAlternately use icacls.\n\nRun \"CMD\" as administrator.\nEnter \"icacls\" followed by the directory.\n\nicacls c:\\\nicacls \"c:\\program files\"\nicacls c:\\windows\n\nThe following results will be displayed as each is entered:\n\nc:\\\nS-1-15-3-65536-1888954469-739942743-1668119174-2468466756-4239452838-1296943325-355587736-700089176 (S,RD,X,RA)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(RX)\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\Authenticated Users:(AD)\nMandatory Label\\High Mandatory Level:(OI)(NP)(IO)(NW)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files\n\nc:\\program files \nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(F)\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files\n\nc:\\windows\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(F)\nNT SERVICE\\TrustedInstaller:(CI)(IO)(F)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(M)\nNT AUTHORITY\\SYSTEM:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(M)\nBUILTIN\\Administrators:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(RX)\nBUILTIN\\Users:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nCREATOR OWNER:(OI)(CI)(IO)(F)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(RX)\nAPPLICATION PACKAGE AUTHORITY\\ALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES:(OI)(CI)(IO)(GR,GE)\nSuccessfully processed 1 files; Failed processing 0 files","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-002165"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253274r1016661","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Network access: Let Everyone permissions apply to anonymous users is set to 'Disabled')\nTest            :   true (System drive root directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\nTest            :   true (Windows installation directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\nTest            :   true (Program Files directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\nTest            :   true (Program Files (x86) directory permissions must conform to minimum requirements.)\n","fix_text":"Maintain the default file system permissions and configure the Security Option: \"Network access: Let everyone permissions apply to anonymous users\" to \"Disabled\" (WN11-SO-000160)."},{"ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253275r958478","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Internet Information Services' feature is not installed)\nTest            :     true ('Internet Information Services Hostable Web Core' feature is not installed)\n","fix_text":"Uninstall \"Internet Information Services\" or \"Internet Information Services Hostable Web Core\" from the system.","uuid":"F1339D15-6C02-1014-8E3C-E3720375944D","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"IIS is not installed by default. Installation of Internet Information System (IIS) may allow unauthorized internet services to be hosted. Websites must only be hosted on servers that have been designed for that purpose and can be adequately secured.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify it has not been installed on the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nIf the entries for \"Internet Information Services\" or \"Internet Information Services Hostable Web Core\" are selected, this is a finding.\n\nIf an application requires IIS or a subset to be installed to function, this needs be documented with the ISSO. In addition, any applicable requirements from the IIS STIG must be addressed.","documentable":"false","severity":"high","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253275","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253275","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253275r958478_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Internet Information System (IIS) or its subcomponents must not be installed on a workstation.","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253275"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-253275","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000100"},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000105","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-253276","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253276r958480_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP) must not be installed on the system.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","id":"V-253276"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253276","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253276"},"documentable":"false","uuid":"F133A13C-6C02-1014-95F1-DB326845821B","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"\"SNMP\" is not installed by default. Some protocols and services do not support required security features, such as encrypting passwords or traffic.","check_content":"Verify SNMP has not been installed.\n\nNavigate to the Windows\\System32 directory.\n\nIf the \"SNMP\" application exists, this is a finding.","rule_id":"SV-253276r958480","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (SNMP Shall Not Be Installed)\n","fix_text":"Uninstall \"Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP)\" from the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows Features on or off\".\nDe-select \"Simple Network Management Protocol (SNMP)\".","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"rule_id":"SV-253277r958478","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Check to make sure the Simple TCP/IP Services server feature is not present.)\n","fix_text":"Uninstall \"Simple TCPIP Services (i.e. echo, daytime etc.)\" from the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows Features on or off\".\nDe-select \"Simple TCPIP Services (i.e. echo, daytime etc.)\".","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"F133A547-6C02-1014-8664-A3739C4B5BF7","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"\"Simple TCP/IP Services\" is not installed by default. Some protocols and services do not support required security features, such as encrypting passwords or traffic.","check_content":"Verify Simple TCP/IP Services has not been installed.\n\nRun \"Services.msc\".\n\nIf \"Simple TCP/IP Services\" is listed, this is a finding.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253277r958478_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Simple TCP/IP Services must not be installed on the system.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253277"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253277"},"group_id":"V-253277","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000110","group_id_src":"V-253277","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},{"ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"The \"Telnet Client\" is not installed by default. Some protocols and services do not support required security features, such as encrypting passwords or traffic.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify Telnet Client has not been installed.\n\nNavigate to the Windows\\System32 directory.\n\nIf the \"telnet\" application exists, this is a finding.","uuid":"F133A97C-6C02-1014-9C01-D2F665C58727","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"rule_id":"SV-253278r958480","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The Telnet Client is not installed on the system)\n","fix_text":"Uninstall \"Telnet Client\" from the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows Features on or off\".\n\nDe-select \"Telnet Client\".","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","group_id_src":"V-253278","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_version":"WN11-00-000115","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-253278","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253278"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"group_tree":{"id":"V-253278","title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253278r958480_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Telnet Client must not be installed on the system."},{"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The TFTP Client must not be installed on the system.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253279r958480_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","id":"V-253279"},"false_positives":"","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-253279","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253279"},"comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000120","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-253279","reference_identifier":"5471","group_title":"SRG-OS-000096-GPOS-00050","weight":"10.0","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (The TFTP Client is not installed on the system)\n","fix_text":"Uninstall \"TFTP Client\" from the system.\n\nRun \"Programs and Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows Features on or off\".\nDe-select \"TFTP Client\".","rule_id":"SV-253279r958480","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133AD91-6C02-1014-AD3D-FDA5E967F4D5","discussion":"The \"TFTP Client\" is not installed by default. Some protocols and services do not support required security features, such as encrypting passwords or traffic.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify TFTP Client has not been installed.\n\nNavigate to the Windows\\System32 directory.\n\nIf the \"TFTP\" application exists, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E"},{"group_tree":{"id":"V-253280","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Software certificate installation files must be removed from Windows 11.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253280r991589_rule","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253280"},"group_id":"V-253280","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000130","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-253280","reference_identifier":"5471","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Software certificate installation files must be removed. Remove .p12 files)\nTest            :   true (Software certificate installation files must be removed. Remove .pfx files)\n","fix_text":"Remove any certificate installation files (*.p12 and *.pfx) found on a system.\n\nNote: This does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files (e.g., Oracle Wallet Manager) or Adobe PreFlight certificate files.","rule_id":"SV-253280r991589","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"Use of software certificates and their accompanying installation files for end users to access resources is less secure than the use of hardware-based certificates.","check_content":"Search all drives for *.p12 and *.pfx files.\n\nIf any files with these extensions exist, this is a finding.\n\nThis does not apply to server-based applications that have a requirement for .p12 certificate files (e.g., Oracle Wallet Manager) or Adobe PreFlight certificate files. Some applications create files with extensions of .p12 that are not certificate installation files. Removal of non-certificate installation files from systems is not required. These must be documented with the ISSO.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133B1A5-6C02-1014-AE85-9BCF7068AAF0"},{"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000135","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253281","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","weight":"10.0","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"A host-based firewall must be installed and enabled on the system.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253281r991589_rule","status":"open","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253281","title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227"},"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253281"},"group_id":"V-253281","comments":null,"documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133B5AB-6C02-1014-8A24-9A44597029C2","check_content":"Determine if a host-based firewall is installed and enabled on the system. If a host-based firewall is not installed and enabled on the system, this is a finding.\n\nThe configuration requirements will be determined by the applicable firewall STIG.","discussion":"A firewall provides a line of defense against attack, allowing or blocking inbound and outbound connections based on a set of rules.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","fix_text":"Install and enable a host-based firewall on the system.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Verify a 3rd party firewall is installed and enabled via Security Center.)\nResult Analysis :        .  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false (Verify Windows defender firewall is enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        enabled = 'False' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'True' \n","rule_id":"SV-253281r991589","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232","id":"V-253282"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Inbound exceptions to the firewall on Windows 11 domain workstations must only allow authorized remote management hosts.","status":"not_reviewed","rule_id_src":"SV-253282r991593_rule","group_id":"V-253282","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:5701"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","rule_version":"WN11-00-000140","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-253282","reference_identifier":"5471","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253282, SV-253282r991593, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00232)\n","fix_text":"Configure firewall exceptions to inbound connections on domain workstations to include only authorized remote management hosts.\n\nConfigure only inbound connection exceptions for authorized remote management hosts.\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security &gt;&gt; Inbound Rules (this link will be in the right pane)\n\nFor any inbound rules that allow connections, configure the Scope for Remote IP address to those of authorized remote management hosts. This may be defined as an IP address, subnet or range. Apply the rule to all firewall profiles.\n\nIf a third-party firewall is used, configure inbound exceptions to only include authorized remote management hosts.","rule_id":"SV-253282r991593","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"documentable":"false","mitigations":"","discussion":"Allowing inbound access to domain workstations from other systems may allow lateral movement across systems if credentials are compromised. Limiting inbound connections only from authorized remote management systems will help limit this exposure.","check_content":"Verify firewall exceptions to inbound connections on domain workstations include only authorized remote management hosts.\n\nIf allowed inbound exceptions are not limited to authorized remote management hosts, this is a finding.\n\nReview inbound firewall exceptions.\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security &gt;&gt; Windows Defender Firewall with Advanced Security &gt;&gt; Inbound Rules (this link will be in the right pane)\n\nFor any inbound rules that allow connections view the Scope for Remote IP address. This may be defined as an IP address, subnet, or range. The rule must apply to all firewall profiles.\n\nIf a third-party firewall is used, ensure comparable settings are in place.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133B9FF-6C02-1014-9D8B-ADE82964B38C"},{"rule_id":"SV-253284r958928","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; \"Enable Structured Exception Handling Overwrite Protection (SEHOP)\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories respectively.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (SEHOP is turned on and properly configured)\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-002824"],"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify SEHOP is turned on.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\Session Manager\\kernel\\\n\nValue Name: DisableExceptionChainValidation\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","mitigations":"","discussion":"Attackers are constantly looking for vulnerabilities in systems and applications. Structured Exception Handling Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) blocks exploits that use the Structured Exception Handling overwrite technique, a common buffer overflow attack.","uuid":"F133BE33-6C02-1014-A27B-D40131612D0F","security_override_guidance":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","id":"V-253284"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253284r958928_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Structured Exception Handling Overwrite Protection (SEHOP) must be enabled.","responsibility":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-253284","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253284","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"severity":"high","legacy_ids":[],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000150","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000433-GPOS-00192","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253284"},{"weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","group_id_src":"V-253285","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_version":"WN11-00-000155","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253285","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253285","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"group_tree":{"id":"V-253285","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_applicable","rule_id_src":"SV-253285r1153425_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Windows PowerShell 2.0 feature must be disabled on the system.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"Windows PowerShell 5.0 added advanced logging features, which can provide additional detail when malware has been run on a system. Disabling the Windows PowerShell 2.0 mitigates against a downgrade attack that evades the Windows PowerShell 5.0 script block logging feature.","check_content":"For Windows 11 version 24H2 and newer, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nRun \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\nGet-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online | Where FeatureName -like *PowerShellv2*\n\nIf either of the following have a \"State\" of \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nFeatureName : MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2\nState : Enabled\nFeatureName : MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2Root\nState : Enabled\n\nAlternately:\nSearch for \"Features\".\n\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nIf \"Windows PowerShell 2.0\" (whether the subcategory of \"Windows PowerShell 2.0 Engine\" is selected or not) is selected, this is a finding.","uuid":"F133C26B-6C02-1014-806E-F6A831D90DE8","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"rule_id":"SV-253285r1153425","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","fix_text":"Disable \"Windows PowerShell 2.0\" on the system.\n\nRun \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\nEnter the following:\nDisable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2Root\n\nThis command must disable both \"MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2Root\" and \"MicrosoftWindowsPowerShellV2\", which correspond to \"Windows PowerShell 2.0\" and \"Windows PowerShell 2.0 Engine\" respectively in \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nAlternately:\nSearch for \"Features\".\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\nDe-select \"Windows PowerShell 2.0\"."},{"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133C6AA-6C02-1014-A1C1-916E2D9C5C46","mitigations":"","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.\n\nDisabling SMBv1 support may prevent access to file or print sharing resources with systems or devices that only support SMBv1. File shares and print services hosted on Windows Server 2003 are an example, however Windows Server 2003 is no longer a supported operating system. Some older Network Attached Storage (NAS) devices may only support SMBv1.","check_content":"Different methods are available to disable SMBv1 on Windows 11. This is the preferred method, however if WN11-00-000165 and WN11-00-000170 are configured, this is NA.\n\nRun \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\nGet-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online | Where FeatureName -eq SMB1Protocol\n\nIf \"State : Enabled\" is returned, this is a finding.\n\nAlternately:\nSearch for \"Features\".\n\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nIf \"SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support\" is selected, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :       true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :         false ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :         true ('Configure SMBv1 Server' is set to 'Disabled')\nCriteria        :       true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :         false ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :         true ('Configure SMBv1 client driver' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Disable driver (recommended)' selected for 'Configure MrxSmb10 driver')\nTest            :     false ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\n","fix_text":"Disable the SMBv1 protocol.\n\nRun \"Windows PowerShell\" with elevated privileges (run as administrator).\n\nEnter the following:\nDisable-WindowsOptionalFeature -Online -FeatureName SMB1Protocol\n\nAlternately:\nSearch for \"Features\".\n\nSelect \"Turn Windows features on or off\".\n\nDe-select \"SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support\".","rule_id":"SV-253286r958478","group_id_src":"V-253286","reference_identifier":"5471","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000160","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253286"},"group_id":"V-253286","comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol must be disabled on the system.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253286r958478_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253286"},"false_positives":""},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :     true ('Configure SMBv1 Server' is set to 'Disabled')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; \"Configure SMBv1 Server\" to \"Disabled\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories, respectively.  \n\nThe system must be restarted for the change to take effect.","rule_id":"SV-253287r958478","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.\n\nDisabling SMBv1 support may prevent access to file or print sharing resources with systems or devices that only support SMBv1. File shares and print services hosted on Windows Server 2003 are an example, however Windows Server 2003 is no longer a supported operating system. Some older network attached devices may only support SMBv1.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Different methods are available to disable SMBv1 on Windows 11, if WN11-00-000160 is configured, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value does not exist or is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\LanmanServer\\Parameters\\\n\nValue Name: SMB1\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133CADE-6C02-1014-87F5-C3237FCF6524","documentable":"false","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253287","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253287","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"id":"V-253287","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol must be disabled on the SMB server.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253287r958478_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-253287","reference_identifier":"5471","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000165","third_party_tools":""},{"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133D201-6C02-1014-83BD-DF91256AEB6C","mitigations":"","discussion":"SMBv1 is a legacy protocol that uses the MD5 algorithm as part of SMB. MD5 is known to be vulnerable to a number of attacks such as collision and preimage attacks as well as not being FIPS compliant.\n\nDisabling SMBv1 support may prevent access to file or print sharing resources with systems or devices that only support SMBv1. File shares and print services hosted on Windows Server 2003 are an example, however Windows Server 2003 is no longer a supported operating system. Some older network attached devices may only support SMBv1.","check_content":"Different methods are available to disable SMBv1 on Windows 11, if WN11-00-000160is configured, this is NA.\n\nIf the following registry value is not configured as specified, this is a finding:\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\mrxsmb10\\\n\nValue Name: Start\n\nType: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000004 (4)","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('SMB 1.0/CIFS File Sharing Support' feature is not installed)\nTest            :     true ('Configure SMBv1 client driver' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Disable driver (recommended)' selected for 'Configure MrxSmb10 driver')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; MS Security Guide &gt;&gt; \"Configure SMBv1 client driver\" to \"Enabled\" with \"Disable driver (recommended)\" selected for \"Configure MrxSmb10 driver\".\n\nThis policy setting requires the installation of the SecGuide custom templates included with the STIG package. \"SecGuide.admx\" and \"SecGuide.adml\" must be copied to the \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions and \\Windows\\PolicyDefinitions\\en-US directories, respectively.  \n\nThe system must be restarted for the changes to take effect.","rule_id":"SV-253288r958478","group_id_src":"V-253288","reference_identifier":"5471","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000170","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253288","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253288","comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Server Message Block (SMB) v1 protocol must be disabled on the SMB client.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253288r958478_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253288"},"false_positives":""},{"uuid":"F133D73A-6C02-1014-9E69-886B321AD03C","security_override_guidance":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Run \"Services.msc\".\n\nLocate the \"Secondary Logon\" service.\n\nIf the \"Startup Type\" is not \"Disabled\" or the \"Status\" is \"Running\", this is a finding.","discussion":"The Secondary Logon service provides a means for entering alternate credentials, typically used to run commands with elevated privileges. Using privileged credentials in a standard user session can expose those credentials to theft.","mitigations":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253289r958478","fix_text":"Configure the \"Secondary Logon\" service \"Startup Type\" to \"Disabled\".","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false (The Secondary Logon service Startup Type is Disabled or the service is uninstalled)\nResult Analysis :          startmode = 'Manual' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'Disabled' \n","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253289","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000175","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253289"},"group_id":"V-253289","rule_id_src":"SV-253289r958478_rule","status":"open","rule_title":"The Secondary Logon service must be disabled on Windows 11.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253289","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"}},{"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253290","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml"},"group_id":"V-253290","comments":null,"responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) must be removed from user rights on Windows 11.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253290r991589_rule","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253290"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-253290","reference_identifier":"5471","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000190","mitigation_control":"","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Orphaned security identifiers (SIDs) must be removed from user rights.)\n","fix_text":"Remove any unresolved SIDs found in User Rights assignments and determined to not be for currently valid accounts or groups by removing the accounts or groups from the appropriate group policy.","rule_id":"SV-253290r991589","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133DB74-6C02-1014-98CE-F0E262BE85DB","mitigations":"","discussion":"Accounts or groups given rights on a system may show up as unresolved SIDs for various reasons including deletion of the accounts or groups. If the account or group objects are reanimated, there is a potential they may still have rights no longer intended. Valid domain accounts or groups may also show up as unresolved SIDs if a connection to the domain cannot be established for some reason.","check_content":"Review the effective User Rights setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Local Policies &gt;&gt; User Rights Assignment.\n\nReview each User Right listed for any unresolved SIDs to determine whether they are valid, such as due to being temporarily disconnected from the domain. (Unresolved SIDs have the format of \"*S-1-..\".)\n\nIf any unresolved SIDs exist and are not for currently valid accounts or groups, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","documentable":"false"},{"group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-253291","reference_identifier":"5471","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000210","third_party_tools":"","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253291","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml"},"group_id":"V-253291","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","id":"V-253291"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Bluetooth must be turned off unless approved by the organization.","status":"not_applicable","rule_id_src":"SV-253291r1153422_rule","mitigations":"","discussion":"If not configured properly, Bluetooth may allow rogue devices to communicate with a system. If a rogue device is paired with a system, there is potential for sensitive information to be compromised.","check_content":"This is NA if the system does not have Bluetooth.\n\nVerify the Bluetooth radio is turned off unless approved by the organization. If it is not, this is a finding.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\PolicyManager\\current\\device\\Connectivity\\\n\nValue Name: AllowBluetooth\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000000 (0)\n\nApproval must be documented with the ISSO.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133DFB1-6C02-1014-AD13-B7E9A8DF80CD","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","fix_text":"Turn off Bluetooth radios not organizationally approved.\n\nFor systems managed by Intune, apply the DOD Windows 11 STIG Settings Catalog (or equivalent Intune policy) found in the Intune policy package available on cyber.mil.\nSteps to create an Intune policy:\n1. Sign in to the Intune admin center &gt;&gt; Devices &gt;&gt; Configuration &gt;&gt; Create &gt;&gt; New Policy.\n2. Platform: Windows 10 and later. Profile type: Settings Catalog, then click \"Create\".\n3. Basics: Provide a Name and Description of the profile, then click \"Next\".\n4. Configuration settings: Click \"+ Add settings\" and search for connectivity under the Settings picker. Under the Connectivity category, check the box next to Allow Bluetooth setting. Choose the first option, \"Disallow Bluetooth\", then click \"Next\".\n5. Scope tags: (optional), then click \"Next\".\n6. Assignments: Assign the policy to Entra security groups that contain the target users or devices, then click \"Next\".\n7. Review + create: Review the deployment summary, then click \"Create\".","rule_id":"SV-253291r1153422"},{"weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253293","rule_version":"WN11-00-000230","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-253293","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253293"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253293"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253293r991589_rule","status":"not_applicable","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The system must notify the user when a Bluetooth device attempts to connect.","responsibility":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"This is NA if the system does not have Bluetooth, or if Bluetooth is turned off per the organizations policy.\n\nSearch for \"Bluetooth\".\nView Bluetooth Settings.\nSelect \"More Bluetooth Options\"\nIf \"Alert me when a new Bluetooth device wants to connect\" is not checked, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"If not configured properly, Bluetooth may allow rogue devices to communicate with a system. If a rogue device is paired with a system, there is potential for sensitive information to be compromised.","uuid":"F133E3E0-6C02-1014-BDD5-EBE875072F42","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"rule_id":"SV-253293r991589","fix_text":"Configure Bluetooth to notify users if devices attempt to connect.\nView Bluetooth Settings.\nEnsure \"Alert me when a new Bluetooth device wants to connect\" is checked.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n"},{"stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Determine whether administrative accounts are prevented from using applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email, except as necessary for local service administration.\n\nThe organization must have a policy that prohibits administrative accounts from using applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email, except as necessary for local service administration. The policy must define specific exceptions for local service administration. These exceptions may include HTTP(S)-based tools that are used for the administration of the local system, services, or attached devices.\n\nTechnical measures such as the removal of applications or application allowlisting must be used where feasible to prevent the use of applications that access the internet. \n\nIf accounts with administrative privileges are not prevented from using applications that access the internet or with potential internet sources, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"Using applications that access the internet or have potential internet sources using administrative privileges exposes a system to compromise. If a flaw in an application is exploited while running as a privileged user, the entire system could be compromised. Web browsers and email are common attack vectors for introducing malicious code and must not be run with an administrative account.\n\nSince administrative accounts may generally change or work around technical restrictions for running a web browser or other applications, it is essential that policy requires administrative accounts to not access the internet or use applications, such as email.\n\nThe policy must define specific exceptions for local service administration. These exceptions may include HTTP(S)-based tools that are used for the administration of the local system, services, or attached devices.\n\nTechnical means such as application allowlisting can be used to enforce the policy to ensure compliance.","uuid":"F133E82D-6C02-1014-9B0E-EA2B6FFAB07D","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"rule_id":"SV-253294r991589","fix_text":"Establish and enforce a policy that prohibits administrative accounts from using applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email. Define specific exceptions for local service administration. These exceptions may include HTTP(S)-based tools that are used for the administration of the local system, services, or attached devices.\n\nImplement technical measures where feasible such as removal of applications or use of application allowlisting to restrict the use of applications that can access the internet.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-253294, SV-253294r991589, SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227)\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253294","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000240","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-253294","check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:7701","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml"},"severity":"high","legacy_ids":[],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000480-GPOS-00227","id":"V-253294"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253294r991589_rule","status":"not_reviewed","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Administrative accounts must not be used with applications that access the internet, such as web browsers, or with potential internet sources, such as email.","responsibility":""},{"ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"For virtual desktop implementations (VDIs) where the virtual desktop instance is deleted or refreshed upon logoff, the organization must enforce that sessions be terminated within 24 hours. This would ensure any data stored on the VM that is not encrypted or covered by Credential Guard is deleted.","check_content":"Verify there is a documented policy or procedure in place that nonpersistent VM sessions do not exceed 24 hours.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  \n\nIf the system is NOT a nonpersistent VM, this is Not Applicable. \n\nFor Azure Virtual Desktop (AVD) implementations with no data at rest, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf there is no such documented policy or procedure in place, this is a finding.","uuid":"F133EC49-6C02-1014-AC57-8438D7312AE8","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"rule_id":"SV-253295r958552","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-253295, SV-253295r958552, SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079)\n","fix_text":"Set nonpersistent VM sessions to not exceed 24 hours.","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079","group_id_src":"V-253295","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_version":"WN11-00-000250","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows11:questionnaire:7901","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml"},"group_id":"V-253295","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"group_tree":{"id":"V-253295","title":"SRG-OS-000185-GPOS-00079"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_reviewed","rule_id_src":"SV-253295r958552_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 nonpersistent VM sessions must not exceed 24 hours.","potential_impacts":""},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-004923","CCI-001891"],"fix_text":"Configure the system to synchronize time with an appropriate DOD time source.\n\nDomain-joined systems use NT5DS to synchronize time from other systems in the domain by default.\n\nIf the system needs to be configured to an NTP server, configure the system to point to an authorized time server by setting the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; System &gt;&gt; Windows Time Service &gt;&gt; Time Providers &gt;&gt; \"Configure Windows NTP Client\" to \"Enabled\", and configure the \"NtpServer\" field to point to an appropriate DOD time server.\n\nThe US Naval Observatory operates stratum 1 time servers, identified at https://www.cnmoc.usff.navy.mil/Our-Commands/United-States-Naval-Observatory/Precise-Time-Department/Network-Time-Protocol-NTP/. Time synchronization will occur through a hierarchy of time servers down to the local level. Clients and lower-level servers will synchronize with an authorized time server in the hierarchy.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Review the Windows time service configuration via PowerShell)\nResult Analysis :        'Type: NTP (Local)' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'NT5DS' \n","rule_id":"SV-253296r1051041","check_content":"Review the Windows time service configuration.\n\nOpen an elevated \"Command Prompt\" (run as administrator).\n\nEnter \"W32tm /query /configuration\".\n\nDomain-joined systems (excluding the domain controller with the PDC emulator role):\n\nIf the value for \"Type\" under \"NTP Client\" is not \"NT5DS\", this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The Windows Time Service controls time synchronization settings. Time synchronization is essential for authentication and auditing purposes. If the Windows Time Service is used, it must synchronize with a secure, authorized time source. Domain-joined systems are automatically configured to synchronize with domain controllers. If an NTP server is configured, it must synchronize with a secure, authorized time source.","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133F071-6C02-1014-B753-A8CDAA47E17B","documentable":"false","group_id":"V-253296","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253296","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"low","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143","id":"V-253296"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The Windows 11 time service must synchronize with an appropriate DOD time source.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253296r1051041_rule","status":"open","group_title":"SRG-OS-000355-GPOS-00143","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253296","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000260","third_party_tools":""},{"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000005","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-253297","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000329-GPOS-00128","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253297r958736_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 account lockout duration must be configured to 15 minutes or greater.","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000329-GPOS-00128","id":"V-253297"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253297","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253297","documentable":"false","uuid":"F133F48B-6C02-1014-ACC8-9BB634812435","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. This parameter specifies the amount of time that an account will remain locked after the specified number of failed logon attempts.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Account lockout duration\" is less than \"15\" minutes (excluding \"0\"), this is a finding.\n\nConfiguring this to \"0\", requiring an administrator to unlock the account, is more restrictive and is not a finding.","rule_id":"SV-253297r958736","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :       false ('Account lockout duration' is set to '0')\nTest            :       true ('Account lockout duration' is set to '15 minutes' or greater)\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is not set to '0')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy &gt;&gt; \"Account lockout duration\" to \"15\" minutes or greater.\n\nA value of \"0\" is also acceptable, requiring an administrator to unlock the account.","ccis":["CCI-002238"],"classification":"Unclassified"},{"weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005","group_id_src":"V-253298","reference_identifier":"5471","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000010","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-253298","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253298"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005","id":"V-253298"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253298r958388_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The number of allowed bad logon attempts must be configured to three or less.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. The higher this value is, the less effective the account lockout feature will be in protecting the local system. The number of bad logon attempts must be reasonably small to minimize the possibility of a successful password attack, while allowing for honest errors made during a normal user logon.","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Account lockout threshold\" is \"0\" or more than \"3\" attempts, this is a finding.","uuid":"F133F884-6C02-1014-905F-A2BCB063A3AA","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000044"],"rule_id":"SV-253298r958388","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is set to '3' or less)\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is not set to '0')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy &gt;&gt; \"Account lockout threshold\" to \"3\" or less invalid logon attempts (excluding \"0\" which is unacceptable)."},{"fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy &gt;&gt; \"Reset account lockout counter after\" to \"15\" minutes.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Reset account lockout counter after' is set to at least the required value)\nTest            :     true ('Account lockout threshold' is not set to '0')\n","rule_id":"SV-253299r958388","ccis":["CCI-000044"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F133FD8F-6C02-1014-8422-EE5422AE4D4E","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Account Lockout Policy.\n\nIf the \"Reset account lockout counter after\" value is less than \"15\" minutes, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The account lockout feature, when enabled, prevents brute-force password attacks on the system. This parameter specifies the period of time that must pass after failed logon attempts before the counter is reset to 0. The smaller this value is, the less effective the account lockout feature will be in protecting the local system.","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The period of time before the bad logon counter is reset must be configured to 15 minutes.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253299r958388_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253299","title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005"},"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-253299","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253299","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000015","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253299","group_title":"SRG-OS-000021-GPOS-00005","weight":"10.0"},{"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253300","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253300","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253300","title":"SRG-OS-000077-GPOS-00045"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253300r1000103_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The password history must be configured to 24 passwords remembered.","responsibility":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000077-GPOS-00045","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253300","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000020","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-004061"],"rule_id":"SV-253300r1000103","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Enforce password history\" to \"24\" passwords remembered.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Enforce password history' is set to '24' passwords or more)\n","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Enforce password history\" is less than \"24\" passwords remembered, this is a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"A system is more vulnerable to unauthorized access when system users recycle the same password several times without being required to change a password to a unique password on a regularly scheduled basis. This enables users to effectively negate the purpose of mandating periodic password changes. The default value is 24 for Windows domain systems. DOD has decided this is the appropriate value for all Windows systems.","uuid":"F13401E0-6C02-1014-8DF1-D0158529DA46","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"documentable":"false","discussion":"The longer a password is in use, the greater the opportunity for someone to gain unauthorized knowledge of the passwords. Scheduled changing of passwords hinders the ability of unauthorized system users to crack passwords and gain access to a system.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Maximum password age\" is greater than \"60\" days, this is a finding. If the value is set to \"0\" (never expires), this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F13405C9-6C02-1014-BF2F-F50FF0DC88A0","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Maximum Password Age is set to 60 days or less, but greater than 0.)\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Maximum Password Age\" to \"60\" days or less (excluding \"0\" which is unacceptable).","rule_id":"SV-253301r1051042","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000199"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000025","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-253301","reference_identifier":"5471","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000076-GPOS-00044","id":"V-253301"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The maximum password age must be configured to 60 days or less.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253301r1051042_rule","group_id":"V-253301","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253301","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium"},{"comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253302","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253302","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000075-GPOS-00043","id":"V-253302"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253302r1051043_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The minimum password age must be configured to at least 1 day.","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000075-GPOS-00043","group_id_src":"V-253302","reference_identifier":"5471","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000030","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000198"],"rule_id":"SV-253302r1051043","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Minimum Password Age' is set to at least '1' day)\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Minimum Password Age\" to at least \"1\" day.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"Permitting passwords to be changed in immediate succession within the same day allows users to cycle passwords through their history database. This enables users to effectively negate the purpose of mandating periodic password changes.","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Minimum password age\" is less than \"1\" day, this is a finding.","uuid":"F13409D5-6C02-1014-85A2-B4864D26D646","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253303"},"group_id":"V-253303","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000078-GPOS-00046","id":"V-253303"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Passwords must, at a minimum, be 14 characters.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253303r1051044_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000078-GPOS-00046","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253303","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AC-000035","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000205"],"fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Minimum password length\" to \"14\" characters.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Minimum password length' is set to at least '14' characters)\n","rule_id":"SV-253303r1051044","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for the \"Minimum password length,\" is less than \"14\" characters, this is a finding.","discussion":"Information systems not protected with strong password schemes (including passwords of minimum length) provide the opportunity for anyone to crack the password, thus gaining access to the system and compromising the device, information, or the local network.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1340E16-6C02-1014-9134-CD2C6FE9F4E2","documentable":"false"},{"documentable":"false","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Password must meet complexity requirements\" is not set to \"Enabled\", this is a finding.\n\nIf the site is using a password filter that requires this setting be set to \"Disabled\" for the filter to be used, this would not be considered a finding.","mitigations":"","discussion":"The use of complex passwords increases their strength against guessing and brute-force attacks. This setting configures the system to verify that newly created passwords conform to the Windows password complexity policy.","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1341471-6C02-1014-896E-F2575A16A68A","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Password must meet complexity requirements\" to \"Enabled\".","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Password must meet complexity requirements' is set to 'Enabled')\n","rule_id":"SV-253304r1051045","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-004066","CCI-000192"],"rule_version":"WN11-AC-000040","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000069-GPOS-00037","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253304","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253304","title":"SRG-OS-000069-GPOS-00037"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The built-in Microsoft password complexity filter must be enabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253304r1051045_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_id":"V-253304","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253304","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium"},{"documentable":"false","check_content":"Verify the effective setting in Local Group Policy Editor.\nRun \"gpedit.msc\".\n\nNavigate to Local Computer Policy &gt;&gt; Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy.\n\nIf the value for \"Store password using reversible encryption\" is not set to \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","discussion":"Storing passwords using reversible encryption is essentially the same as storing clear-text versions of the passwords. For this reason, this policy must never be enabled.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F13419D3-6C02-1014-A8DD-A8DB7B2BBB44","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Account Policies &gt;&gt; Password Policy &gt;&gt; \"Store passwords using reversible encryption\" to \"Disabled\".","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Store password using reversible encryption' is set to 'Disabled')\n","rule_id":"SV-253305r1051046","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-004062","CCI-000196"],"rule_version":"WN11-AC-000045","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253305","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000073-GPOS-00041","id":"V-253305"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Reversible password encryption must be disabled.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253305r1051046_rule","status":"not_a_finding","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253305"},"group_id":"V-253305","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"high"},{"stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Logon &gt;&gt; Credential Validation - Failure","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nCredential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","mitigations":"","uuid":"F1341E04-6C02-1014-A76C-DECA0DAE9E0E","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"rule_id":"SV-253306r991570","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Logon &gt;&gt; \"Audit Credential Validation\" with \"Failure\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Failure')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253306","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000005","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-253306","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253306"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253306","title":"SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253306r991570_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Logon - Credential Validation failures.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":""},{"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Logon &gt;&gt; \"Audit Credential Validation\" with \"Success\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Success')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Credential Validation' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","rule_id":"SV-253307r991570","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1342220-6C02-1014-B597-EF3E2855E39E","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Logon &gt;&gt; Credential Validation - Success","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nCredential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-253307","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253307"},"comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Logon - Credential Validation successes.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253307r991570_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253307","title":"SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203"},"reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253307","group_title":"SRG-OS-000458-GPOS-00203","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000010","mitigation_control":""},{"rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Management - Security Group Management successes.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253308r971541_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000337-GPOS-00129","id":"V-253308"},"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253308","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253308","comments":null,"third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000030","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253308","group_title":"SRG-OS-000337-GPOS-00129","weight":"10.0","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt; \"Audit Security Group Management\" with \"Success\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Audit Security Group Management' is set to 'Success' or 'Success and Failure')\n","rule_id":"SV-253308r971541","ccis":["CCI-001914"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1342648-6C02-1014-8C3E-AE422900655F","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; Security Group Management - Success","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSecurity Group Management records events such as creating, deleting or changing of security groups, including changes in group members.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":""},{"documentable":"false","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; User Account Management - Failure","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nUser Account Management records events such as creating, changing, deleting, renaming, disabling, or enabling user accounts.","mitigations":"","uuid":"F1342A3C-6C02-1014-A8C2-80AA87DA8D79","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-253309r958566","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt; \"Audit User Account Management\" with \"Failure\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit User Account Management' is set to 'Failure')\nTest            :     true ('Audit User Account Management' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001314"],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000035","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253309","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000206-GPOS-00084","id":"V-253309"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253309r958566_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Management - User Account Management failures.","responsibility":"","comments":null,"group_id":"V-253309","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253309"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[]},{"stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nAccount Management &gt;&gt; User Account Management - Success","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nUser Account Management records events such as creating, changing, deleting, renaming, disabling, or enabling user accounts.","mitigations":"","uuid":"F1342E34-6C02-1014-85FF-E29093E05C0F","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-001403"],"rule_id":"SV-253310r991551","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Account Management &gt;&gt; \"Audit User Account Management\" with \"Success\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit User Account Management' is set to 'Success')\nTest            :     true ('Audit User Account Management' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253310","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000040","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253310","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253310","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000239-GPOS-00089","id":"V-253310"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253310r991551_rule","status":"not_a_finding","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Account Management - User Account Management successes.","potential_impacts":"","responsibility":""},{"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings must be set to Enabled)\nTest            :   true (Detailed Tracking - Plug and Play Events successes.)\n","fix_text":"Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Detailed Tracking &gt;&gt; \"Audit PNP Activity\" with \"Success\" selected.","rule_id":"SV-253311r1051047","ccis":["CCI-000172","CCI-003938","CCI-001814"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"F1343250-6C02-1014-995B-B55761200D4E","mitigations":"","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nPlug and Play activity records events related to the successful connection of external devices.","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nDetailed Tracking &gt;&gt; Plug and Play Events - Success","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Detailed Tracking - PNP Activity successes.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253311r1051047_rule","group_tr