p_id_src":"V-253318","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000080","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true (Audit - Special Logon - Success only)\nTest            :     false (Audit - Special Logon - Success and Failure)\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Logon/Logoff &gt;&gt; \"Audit Special Logon\" with \"Success\" selected.","rule_id":"SV-253318r991578","mitigations":"","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSpecial Logon records special logons which have administrative privileges and can be used to elevate processes.","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nLogon/Logoff &gt;&gt; Special Logon - Success","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"e5653a8e-214b-11f1-8a56-add5940230b0","documentable":"false"},{"group_id_src":"V-253319","reference_identifier":"5471","group_title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000081","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_id":"V-253319","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253319"},"comments":null,"responsibility":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit Object Access - File Share failures.","potential_impacts":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253319r991572_rule","group_tree":{"id":"V-253319","title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206"},"false_positives":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"e5654f42-214b-11f1-8a56-c3742c976bca","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuditing file shares records events related to connection to shares on a system including system shares such as C$.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen PowerShell or a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following:\nObject Access &gt;&gt; File Share - Failure\n\nIf the system does not audit the above, this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"classification":"Unclassified","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit File Share' is set to 'Failure')\nTest            :     true ('Audit File Share' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit File Share\" with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_id":"SV-253319r991572"},{"ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuditing file shares records events related to connection to shares on a system including system shares such as C$.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen PowerShell or a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following:\n\nObject Access &gt;&gt; File Share - Success\n\nIf the system does not audit the above, this is a finding.","uuid":"e565578a-214b-11f1-8a56-c3ab3dd6bb87","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"rule_id":"SV-253320r991572","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Audit File Share' is set to 'Success')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit File Share\" with \"Success\" selected.","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","group_id_src":"V-253320","reference_identifier":"5471","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000082","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253320"},"group_id":"V-253320","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"group_tree":{"id":"V-253320","title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253320r991572_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit Object Access - File Share successes.","potential_impacts":""},{"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253321","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253321"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"group_tree":{"id":"V-253321","title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253321r991572_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit Object Access - Other Object Access Events successes.","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","group_id_src":"V-253321","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000083","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":"","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"rule_id":"SV-253321r991572","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Other Object Access Events' is set to 'Success')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Other Object Access Events' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit Other Object Access Events\" with \"Success\" selected.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuditing for other object access records events related to the management of task scheduler jobs and COM+ objects.","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen PowerShell or a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\n\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following:\n\nObject Access &gt;&gt; Other Object Access Events - Success\n\nIf the system does not audit the above, this is a finding.","uuid":"e5655f47-214b-11f1-8a56-f3a847e88d5e","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false"},{"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000084","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","group_id_src":"V-253322","reference_identifier":"5471","group_tree":{"id":"V-253322","title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253322r991572_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit Object Access - Other Object Access Events failures.","comments":null,"group_id":"V-253322","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253322","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuditing for other object access records events related to the management of task scheduler jobs and COM+ objects.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n\nOpen PowerShell or a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following:\nObject Access &gt;&gt; Other Object Access Events - Failure\n\nIf the system does not audit the above, this is a finding.","uuid":"e56566b3-214b-11f1-8a56-f84ef171d7ea","security_override_guidance":"","rule_id":"SV-253322r991572","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Other Object Access Events' is set to 'Failure')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Other Object Access Events' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit Other Object Access Events\" with \"Failure\" selected.","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000172"]},{"severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253323","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253323"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253323r991583_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Object Access - Removable Storage failures.","group_tree":{"id":"V-253323","title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219"},"false_positives":"","group_id_src":"V-253323","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000085","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253323r991583","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings must be set to Enabled)\nTest            :   true (Removable Storage - Failure)\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit Removable Storage\" with \"Failure\" selected.","uuid":"e5656e6e-214b-11f1-8a56-c8d605c76d93","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","mitigations":"","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuditing object access for removable media records events related to access attempts on file system objects on removable storage devices.","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nObject Access &gt;&gt; Removable Storage - Failure\n\nSome virtual machines may generate excessive audit events for access to the virtual hard disk itself when this setting is enabled. This may be set to Not Configured in such cases and would not be a finding. This must be documented with the ISSO to include mitigations such as monitoring or restricting any actual removable storage connected to the VM.","documentable":"false"},{"group_id_src":"V-253324","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219","third_party_tools":"","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000090","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-253324","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.windows:def:253324"},"status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253324r991583_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Object Access - Removable Storage successes.","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253324","title":"SRG-OS-000474-GPOS-00219"},"false_positives":"","uuid":"e56575f9-214b-11f1-8a56-b50e135b34c0","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuditing object access for removable media records events related to access attempts on file system objects on removable storage devices.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings (Windows Vista or later) to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\"\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nObject Access &gt;&gt; Removable Storage - Success\n\nSome virtual machines may generate excessive audit events for access to the virtual hard disk itself when this setting is enabled. This may be set to Not Configured in such cases and would not be a finding. This must be documented with the ISSO to include mitigations such as monitoring or restricting any actual removable storage connected to the VM.","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"classification":"Unclassified","rule_id":"SV-253324r991583","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings must be set to Enabled)\nTest            :   true (Removable Storage - Success)\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit Removable Storage\" with \"Success\" selected."},{"stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPolicy Change &gt;&gt; Audit Policy Change - Success","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAudit Policy Change records events related to changes in audit policy.","mitigations":"","uuid":"e5657de6-214b-11f1-8a56-aff36be257e1","security_override_guidance":"","documentable":"false","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"rule_id":"SV-253325r991572","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Policy Change &gt;&gt; \"Audit Policy Change\" with \"Success\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true ('Audit Audit Policy Change' is set to 'Success')\nTest            :     false ('Audit Audit Policy Change' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253325","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000100","third_party_tools":"","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253325"},"group_id":"V-253325","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"false_positives":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","id":"V-253325"},"rule_id_src":"SV-253325r991572_rule","status":"not_a_finding","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Policy Change - Audit Policy Change successes.","responsibility":""},{"group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","id":"V-253326"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Policy Change - Authentication Policy Change successes.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253326r991572_rule","group_id":"V-253326","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253326"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000105","third_party_tools":"","group_title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-253326","reference_identifier":"5471","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Audit Authentication Policy Change' is set to 'Success' or 'Success and Failure')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Policy Change &gt;&gt; \"Audit Authentication Policy Change\" with \"Success\" selected.","rule_id":"SV-253326r991572","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"documentable":"false","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuthentication Policy Change records events related to changes in authentication policy including Kerberos policy and Trust changes.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPolicy Change &gt;&gt; Authentication Policy Change - Success","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"e56585df-214b-11f1-8a56-863b746cd109"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Policy Change &gt;&gt; \"Audit Authorization Policy Change\" with \"Success\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     true (Audit - Audit Policy Change - Success only)\nTest            :     false (Audit - Audit Policy Change - Success and Failure)\n","rule_id":"SV-253327r991572","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective. \n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\n-Open a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\n-Enter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding.\n\nPolicy Change &gt;&gt; Authorization Policy Change - Success","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nAuthorization Policy Change records events related to changes in user rights, such as create a token object.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"e5658dcc-214b-11f1-8a56-8b875d4de423","documentable":"false","group_id":"V-253327","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253327"},"comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-253327","title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206"},"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Policy Change - Authorization Policy Change successes.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-253327r991572_rule","status":"not_a_finding","group_title":"SRG-OS-000462-GPOS-00206","weight":"10.0","reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-253327","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000107","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"rule_id":"SV-253328r958732","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Failure' or 'Success and Failure')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" with \"Failure\" selected.","classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-002234"],"documentable":"false","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior.\n\nSensitive Privilege Use records events related to use of sensitive privileges, such as \"Act as part of the operating system\" or \"Debug programs\".","mitigations":"","check_content":"Security Option \"Audit: Force audit policy subcategory settings to override audit policy category settings\" must be set to \"Enabled\" (WN11-SO-000030) for the detailed auditing subcategories to be effective.\n\nUse the AuditPol tool to review the current Audit Policy configuration:\nOpen a Command Prompt with elevated privileges (\"Run as Administrator\").\nEnter \"AuditPol /get /category:*\".\n\nCompare the AuditPol settings with the following. If the system does not audit the following, this is a finding:\n\nPrivilege Use &gt;&gt; Sensitive Privilege Use - Failure","uuid":"e5659983-214b-11f1-8a56-bf4f72f5d53b","security_override_guidance":"","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","id":"V-253328"},"false_positives":"","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-253328r958732_rule","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"The system must be configured to audit Privilege Use - Sensitive Privilege Use failures.","comments":null,"check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:253328","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"group_id":"V-253328","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"mitigation_control":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000110","third_party_tools":"","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000327-GPOS-00127","group_id_src":"V-253328","reference_identifier":"5471"},{"ccis":["CCI-000172"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" with \"Success\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true ('Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Suc