nfigure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; \"Audit Registry\" with \"Success\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Registry' is set to 'Success')\nResult Analysis :          registry = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS' \nTest            :     false ('Audit Registry' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\nResult Analysis :          registry = 'AUDIT_NONE' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'AUDIT_SUCCESS_FAILURE' \n","rule_id":"SV-278931r1135311","check_content":"Verify that Audit Registry auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Object Access &gt;&gt; Audit Registry. \n\nIf \"Audit Registry\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"e56a4204-214b-11f1-8a56-b670fbe88fc6","documentable":"false"},{"reference_identifier":"5471","group_id_src":"V-278932","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","weight":"10.0","third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000587","mitigation_control":"","legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:278932"},"group_id":"V-278932","comments":null,"potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use successes.","responsibility":"","rule_id_src":"SV-278932r1141916_rule","status":"not_a_finding","false_positives":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-278932","title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031"},"security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"e56a46e5-214b-11f1-8a56-fd29860bc160","check_content":"Verify that Audit Sensitive Privilege Use auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; Audit Sensitive Privilege Use. \n\nIf \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" is not set to \"Success\", this is a finding.","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","mitigations":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","ia_controls":"","documentable":"false","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"classification":"Unclassified","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; Audit Sensitive Privilege Use with \"Success\" selected.","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Success')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","rule_id":"SV-278932r1141916"},{"classification":"Unclassified","ccis":["CCI-000172"],"finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :     false ('Audit Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Failure')\nTest            :     true ('Audit Sensitive Privilege Use' is set to 'Success' and 'Failure')\n","fix_text":"Configure the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; Audit Sensitive Privilege Use with \"Failure\" selected.","rule_id":"SV-278933r1141919","mitigations":"","discussion":"Maintaining an audit trail of system activity logs can help identify configuration errors, troubleshoot service disruptions, and analyze compromises that have occurred, as well as detect attacks. Audit logs are necessary to provide a trail of evidence in case the system or network is compromised. Collecting this data is essential for analyzing the security of information assets and detecting signs of suspicious and unexpected behavior. Credential validation records events related to validation tests on credentials for a user account logon.","check_content":"Verify that Audit Sensitive Privilege Use auditing has been enabled: \n\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Windows Settings &gt;&gt; Security Settings &gt;&gt; Advanced Audit Policy Configuration &gt;&gt; System Audit Policies &gt;&gt; Privilege Use &gt;&gt; Audit Sensitive Privilege Use. \n\nIf \"Audit Sensitive Privilege Use\" is not set to \"Failure\", this is a finding.","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","security_override_guidance":"","uuid":"e56a4ba1-214b-11f1-8a56-b9ab8a6d57ac","documentable":"false","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:278933"},"group_id":"V-278933","comments":null,"legacy_ids":[],"severity":"medium","group_tree":{"title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","id":"V-278933"},"false_positives":"","responsibility":"","potential_impacts":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 must be configured to audit sensitive privilege use failures.","status":"not_a_finding","rule_id_src":"SV-278933r1141919_rule","group_title":"SRG-OS-000062-GPOS-00031","weight":"10.0","group_id_src":"V-278933","reference_identifier":"5471","rule_version":"WN11-AU-000588","mitigation_control":"","third_party_tools":""},{"status":"open","rule_id_src":"SV-279688r1153564_rule","responsibility":"","rule_title":"Windows 11 systems must block consumer account user authentication.","potential_impacts":"","group_tree":{"id":"V-279688","title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049"},"false_positives":"","severity":"medium","legacy_ids":[],"comments":null,"group_id":"V-279688","check_content_ref":{"name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.windows11:def:279688","href":"U_MS_Windows_11_V2R7_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval.xml"},"third_party_tools":"","rule_version":"WN11-00-000126","mitigation_control":"","group_id_src":"V-279688","reference_identifier":"5471","weight":"10.0","group_title":"SRG-OS-000095-GPOS-00049","rule_id":"SV-279688r1153564","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T08:20:30\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     false ('Prevent enabling lock screen camera' is set to 'Enabled')\nResult Analysis :          Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftAccount\\DisableUserAuth'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","fix_text":"Configure the following Group Policy:\nComputer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Microsoft Account \"block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nFor systems managed by Intune, apply the DOD Windows 11 STIG Settings Catalog (or equivalent Intune policy) found in the Intune policy package available on cyber.mil.\nSteps to create an Intune policy:\n1. Sign in to the Intune admin center &gt;&gt; Devices &gt;&gt; Configuration &gt;&gt; Create &gt;&gt; New Policy.\n2. Platform: Windows 10 and later. Profile type: Settings Catalog, then click \"Create\".\n3. Basics: Provide a Name and Description of the profile, then click \"Next\".\n4. Configuration settings: Click \"+ Add settings\" and search for consumer under the Settings picker. Under the Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Microsoft account category, check the box next to \"Block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\". Click the Enabled radio button, then click \"Next\".\n5. Scope tags: (optional), then click \"Next\".\n6. Assignments: Assign the policy to Entra security groups that contain the target users or devices, then click \"Next\".\n7. Review + create: Review the deployment summary, then click \"Create\".","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"classification":"Unclassified","documentable":"false","uuid":"e56a759f-214b-11f1-8a56-f59a9ae0d55d","security_override_guidance":"","ia_controls":"","stig_uuid":"F106633E-6C02-1014-9BE4-8FEE92E1E99E","discussion":"It is detrimental for operating systems to provide, or install by default, functionality exceeding requirements or mission objectives. These unnecessary capabilities or services are often overlooked and therefore, may remain unsecured. They increase the risk to the platform by providing additional attack vectors.\n\nOperating systems are capable of providing a wide variety of functions and services. Some of the functions and services, provided by default, may not be necessary to support essential organizational operations (e.g., key missions, functions).\n\nThe Copilot Rewrite functionality within Notepad and Image Generation within Paint is dependent upon the use of AI credits from a Microsoft 365 Personal or Family subscription. Organizational users must not use personal accounts to login to applications on enterprise machines.","mitigations":"","check_content":"Verify the \"block all consumer Microsoft account user authentication\" is enabled.\n\nRegistry Hive: HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\nRegistry Path: \\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\MicrosoftAccount\n\nValue Name: DisableUserAuth\n\nValue Type: REG_DWORD\nValue: 0x00000001 (1)\n\nIf the registry value is not \"1\", this is a finding."}],"reference_identifier":"5471"}]}